WEBVTT

00:00.000 --> 00:08.000
At the seaside.

00:12.000 --> 00:13.000
A cup of tea.

00:13.000 --> 00:15.000
Yes, dear.

00:18.000 --> 00:20.000
Here you are.

00:20.000 --> 00:21.000
Yes, dear.

00:21.000 --> 00:23.000
Here you are.

00:23.000 --> 00:25.000
Yes, dear.

00:31.000 --> 00:34.000
Would you like some jam, mother?

00:34.000 --> 00:36.000
I don't like ham, Nancy.

00:36.000 --> 00:38.000
You know I don't eat meat.

00:38.000 --> 00:40.000
You said jam, mother.

00:40.000 --> 00:41.000
Not ham.

00:41.000 --> 00:43.000
Would you like some jam, mother?

00:43.000 --> 00:45.000
Yes, please, Nancy.

00:45.000 --> 00:47.000
I hope it's strawberry jam.

00:47.000 --> 00:49.000
I like strawberry jam.

00:49.000 --> 00:51.000
I don't like raspberry jam.

00:51.000 --> 00:53.000
And I don't like plum jam.

00:53.000 --> 00:54.000
And I don't like...

00:54.000 --> 00:56.000
Yes, I know, mother.

00:56.000 --> 00:58.000
I only buy strawberry jam.

00:58.000 --> 01:02.000
Yes, strawberry jam for the last five years.

01:02.000 --> 01:03.000
Just for her.

01:03.000 --> 01:04.000
Not again.

01:04.000 --> 01:07.000
There are other people in this family, dear.

01:07.000 --> 01:09.000
I like raspberry jam.

01:09.000 --> 01:11.000
Well, you can do the shopping next week.

01:11.000 --> 01:13.000
And then you buy what you want.

01:13.000 --> 01:15.000
You know I have no time.

01:15.000 --> 01:17.000
No, dear.

01:17.000 --> 01:20.000
I don't like strawberry jam all the time.

01:20.000 --> 01:22.000
Not again.

01:22.000 --> 01:27.000
We're going on a nice family seaside holiday for a week.

01:27.000 --> 01:30.000
You can have raspberry jam for breakfast in the hotel.

01:30.000 --> 01:33.000
And mum can have strawberry jam, okay?

01:33.000 --> 01:34.000
Yes, dear.

01:34.000 --> 01:39.000
Oh, here you are, Boris.

01:39.000 --> 01:41.000
Have my jam sandwich.

01:44.000 --> 01:46.000
Don't give Boris your sandwich.

01:46.000 --> 01:48.000
You know what happens.

01:48.000 --> 01:50.000
He looks hungry.

01:50.000 --> 01:52.000
I don't think you give him enough food.

01:52.000 --> 01:54.000
It's not a horse, mum.

01:54.000 --> 01:56.000
It's not a real dog.

01:56.000 --> 01:59.000
A real dog is a golden retriever.

01:59.000 --> 02:02.000
I like golden retrievers.

02:02.000 --> 02:05.000
Boris is noisy and smelly.

02:05.000 --> 02:06.000
That reminds me.

02:06.000 --> 02:09.000
Why are we taking your mother on holiday?

02:09.000 --> 02:11.000
You know what happened last year?

02:11.000 --> 02:13.000
Not again, Pete.

02:13.000 --> 02:15.000
We can't leave her alone in the house.

02:15.000 --> 02:16.000
Why not?

02:16.000 --> 02:18.000
What's he saying about me?

02:18.000 --> 02:20.000
I know he's talking about me.

02:20.000 --> 02:22.000
I know he's talking about me.

02:22.000 --> 02:24.000
He doesn't like me.

02:24.000 --> 02:26.000
No, mother. It's okay.

02:26.000 --> 02:29.000
He's talking about the lovely holiday together.

02:29.000 --> 02:30.000
No, he's not.

02:30.000 --> 02:31.000
Yes, he is.

02:31.000 --> 02:32.000
No, I'm not.

02:32.000 --> 02:33.000
No, he's not.

02:33.000 --> 02:35.000
Yes, he is.

02:35.000 --> 02:37.000
I'll stop this, everyone.

02:37.000 --> 02:41.000
I want a nice, relaxing breakfast, please.

02:41.000 --> 02:43.000
We have a long journey today.

02:43.000 --> 02:47.000
Please try to be nice to each other for one minute.

02:48.000 --> 02:51.000
Not again. I can't believe it.

02:51.000 --> 02:53.000
Stop that, Josephine.

02:53.000 --> 02:55.000
It's not nice at the breakfast table.

02:55.000 --> 02:56.000
Why not?

02:56.000 --> 02:57.000
Because I say so.

02:57.000 --> 03:00.000
I tell you, every morning, not to do that.

03:00.000 --> 03:01.000
I want to.

03:01.000 --> 03:03.000
Robbie's hungry.

03:03.000 --> 03:06.000
You can feed it in your room in its cage.

03:06.000 --> 03:08.000
Please keep it in its cage.

03:08.000 --> 03:10.000
You get lonely.

03:10.000 --> 03:11.000
I don't know why.

03:11.000 --> 03:12.000
She has a pet rat.

03:12.000 --> 03:13.000
It's unhealthy.

03:13.000 --> 03:15.000
We said Josephine can have a pet.

03:15.000 --> 03:16.000
Don't you remember?

03:16.000 --> 03:18.000
Of course I remember.

03:18.000 --> 03:21.000
But a cat or a dog, not a parasite.

03:21.000 --> 03:23.000
I like Robbie.

03:23.000 --> 03:24.000
He's sweet.

03:24.000 --> 03:25.000
It smells.

03:25.000 --> 03:26.000
No, it doesn't.

03:26.000 --> 03:27.000
Yes, it does.

03:27.000 --> 03:29.000
I like Robbie.

03:29.000 --> 03:30.000
He's sweet.

03:30.000 --> 03:32.000
The rat is not coming on holiday.

03:32.000 --> 03:33.000
Why not?

03:33.000 --> 03:35.000
Because it's not.

03:35.000 --> 03:37.000
Nancy, speak to your daughter, please.

03:37.000 --> 03:39.000
Why is it always me?

03:39.000 --> 03:41.000
No, Josephine.

03:41.000 --> 03:42.000
It's not coming.

03:42.000 --> 03:44.000
It can't stay in the hotel.

03:44.000 --> 03:46.000
But I like Robbie.

03:46.000 --> 03:49.000
Be quiet, Mother.

03:49.000 --> 03:52.000
After breakfast, take it to your friend.

03:52.000 --> 03:54.000
She can look after it.

03:54.000 --> 03:56.000
But she's going out.

03:56.000 --> 03:58.000
Just do as I say, Josephine.

03:58.000 --> 04:00.000
Don't argue.

04:00.000 --> 04:01.000
I like him.

04:01.000 --> 04:03.000
He's sweet.

04:03.000 --> 04:04.000
Thank you, Grand.

04:04.000 --> 04:06.000
You see?

04:06.000 --> 04:07.000
Grandma.

04:07.000 --> 04:09.000
You see?

04:09.000 --> 04:11.000
Grand thinks Robbie is sweet.

04:11.000 --> 04:13.000
Maybe because it looks like her.

04:13.000 --> 04:15.000
He's talking about me again.

04:15.000 --> 04:17.000
What did he say, Nancy?

04:17.000 --> 04:19.000
It's not good for my heart.

04:19.000 --> 04:21.000
He knows I have high blood pressure.

04:21.000 --> 04:23.000
I said that it looks.

04:23.000 --> 04:24.000
Not again, Pete.

04:24.000 --> 04:28.000
The rat is not coming with us.

04:28.000 --> 04:31.000
You heard your mother, Josephine.

04:31.000 --> 04:32.000
I like him.

04:32.000 --> 04:33.000
It's sweet.

04:33.000 --> 04:36.000
I am getting very, very angry.

04:36.000 --> 04:39.000
You will find me in the garage cleaning the car.

04:39.000 --> 04:41.000
It is the only place in this house

04:41.000 --> 04:44.000
where I can find some peace and quiet.

04:44.000 --> 04:48.000
Why did you marry him, Nancy?

04:48.000 --> 04:51.000
Not again, Mum.

04:51.000 --> 04:53.000
I liked Jonathan.

04:53.000 --> 04:56.000
You know he lived next door.

04:56.000 --> 04:58.000
He liked you, too.

04:58.000 --> 05:00.000
He had very nice tea.

05:00.000 --> 05:03.000
He went to university.

05:03.000 --> 05:05.000
He's a doctor.

05:05.000 --> 05:07.000
Lovely house.

05:07.000 --> 05:09.000
I met his mother last week.

05:09.000 --> 05:11.000
He's...

05:11.000 --> 05:13.000
Not again, Mum.

05:21.000 --> 05:23.000
Go in your own room, Josephine.

05:23.000 --> 05:25.000
Pack your suitcase.

05:25.000 --> 05:27.000
I want to pack my bag now.

05:27.000 --> 05:29.000
I don't want to go on holiday.

05:29.000 --> 05:31.000
It's math.

05:31.000 --> 05:34.000
The same totally naff town.

05:34.000 --> 05:36.000
The same naff hotel.

05:36.000 --> 05:37.000
The same naff food.

05:37.000 --> 05:39.000
That's enough, Josephine.

05:39.000 --> 05:40.000
You are coming with the family.

05:40.000 --> 05:43.000
You're too young to stay at home alone.

05:43.000 --> 05:46.000
Why don't we go to Spain on Mallorca?

05:46.000 --> 05:49.000
All my friends go abroad.

05:49.000 --> 05:53.000
Why do we always go to bloody, stupid Blackpool?

05:53.000 --> 05:54.000
I hate it.

05:54.000 --> 05:57.000
I want to go to somewhere where I can chill out

05:57.000 --> 05:59.000
and meet some fit guys.

05:59.000 --> 06:01.000
Blackpool is nice.

06:01.000 --> 06:03.000
We can sit on the beach.

06:03.000 --> 06:05.000
We can go to the fair.

06:05.000 --> 06:07.000
We can ride on a donkey.

06:07.000 --> 06:08.000
We can have fun.

06:08.000 --> 06:10.000
I don't want to sodding donkey.

06:10.000 --> 06:13.000
Mum, I am 15 years old.

06:13.000 --> 06:16.000
I don't want to ride on a naffing donkey.

06:16.000 --> 06:19.000
I want to go to discos.

06:19.000 --> 06:20.000
Meet people.

06:20.000 --> 06:22.000
Have fun.

06:22.000 --> 06:24.000
No, this year it is Blackpool.

06:24.000 --> 06:25.000
That is final.

06:25.000 --> 06:28.000
No more arguments and stop using those terrible words.

06:28.000 --> 06:30.000
I say what I want.

06:30.000 --> 06:32.000
But why do we always go to Blackpool?

06:32.000 --> 06:34.000
Because...

06:34.000 --> 06:36.000
Because...

06:36.000 --> 06:39.000
Because we do.

06:39.000 --> 06:42.000
Don't take that dress, Mum. It's too short.

06:42.000 --> 06:44.000
I don't think it is.

06:44.000 --> 06:45.000
Yes, it is.

06:45.000 --> 06:48.000
Everyone can see your fat legs.

06:48.000 --> 06:50.000
I'm taking it.

06:50.000 --> 06:52.000
What's this?

06:52.000 --> 06:54.000
Why are you taking this?

06:54.000 --> 06:56.000
You never wear this for Dad.

06:56.000 --> 06:57.000
Is it new?

06:57.000 --> 06:58.000
Give it to me, Josephine.

06:58.000 --> 07:00.000
I bought it for the holiday.

07:00.000 --> 07:02.000
Does Dad know you bought it?

07:02.000 --> 07:04.000
Dad, Dad, come here.

07:04.000 --> 07:05.000
Stop it, Josephine.

07:05.000 --> 07:07.000
No, I didn't tell your father.

07:07.000 --> 07:10.000
It's a surprise.

07:10.000 --> 07:12.000
Why did you buy it?

07:12.000 --> 07:14.000
It looks very expensive.

07:14.000 --> 07:18.000
You are much too old to wear it.

07:18.000 --> 07:20.000
I know.

07:20.000 --> 07:23.000
It's that slimy Italian manager at the hotel.

07:23.000 --> 07:25.000
What's his name?

07:25.000 --> 07:27.000
I know.

07:27.000 --> 07:29.000
squeegee or something.

07:29.000 --> 07:31.000
I don't know what you're talking about, Josephine.

07:31.000 --> 07:33.000
Yes, you do.

07:33.000 --> 07:35.000
Italian manager, we meet every year.

07:35.000 --> 07:38.000
Oh, yes.

07:38.000 --> 07:41.000
His name is not squeegee.

07:41.000 --> 07:43.000
It's Luigi.

07:43.000 --> 07:46.000
Luigi Bertolini.

07:46.000 --> 07:48.000
And he's not slimy.

07:48.000 --> 07:50.000
He has charming and kind.

07:50.000 --> 07:52.000
I don't like him.

07:52.000 --> 07:54.000
He's got spots and he smells like a perfume factory.

07:54.000 --> 07:57.000
They're fickle, it's not spots.

07:57.000 --> 08:00.000
Did you do it with him last year, Mum?

08:00.000 --> 08:02.000
No, I didn't.

08:02.000 --> 08:05.000
What a thing to say.

08:05.000 --> 08:07.000
You know how much I love your father.

08:07.000 --> 08:09.000
Why do you say that, Josephine?

08:09.000 --> 08:11.000
No reason, Mum.

08:11.000 --> 08:13.000
No reason.

08:13.000 --> 08:16.000
It's just that I bought a new bikini for the holiday.

08:16.000 --> 08:18.000
What do you think?

08:18.000 --> 08:19.000
Oh!

08:19.000 --> 08:22.000
Oh, no, Mother.

08:22.000 --> 08:24.000
What's the matter?

08:24.000 --> 08:25.000
I like it.

08:25.000 --> 08:27.000
Red is a nice colour.

08:27.000 --> 08:31.000
The woman in the shop said that red is the colour for this year.

08:31.000 --> 08:34.000
It's not the colour that's the problem.

08:34.000 --> 08:36.000
So what's the matter then?

08:36.000 --> 08:39.000
The problem is the bikini, Mother.

08:39.000 --> 08:42.000
It's, um, very small.

08:42.000 --> 08:45.000
Yes, I want to get a suntan this year.

08:45.000 --> 08:48.000
It's Blackpool, Mother, not the Caribbean.

08:48.000 --> 08:51.000
It rained last year and the year before.

08:51.000 --> 08:55.000
But don't you think you're a bit old for that bikini?

08:55.000 --> 08:59.000
John at the Bingo Club said I have a good body.

08:59.000 --> 09:02.000
John? From across the road?

09:02.000 --> 09:05.000
He's totally blind. He has a white stick.

09:05.000 --> 09:06.000
Yes, I know.

09:06.000 --> 09:09.000
But he feels I have a great body.

09:12.000 --> 09:17.000
But a cloudier shiffer has a red bikini just like this one.

09:17.000 --> 09:19.000
I saw it on television.

09:19.000 --> 09:22.000
Mother, you cannot wear that.

09:22.000 --> 09:25.000
It's super grand.

09:25.000 --> 09:28.000
Don't listen to Nancy.

09:28.000 --> 09:32.000
Oh, please, wear it on the beach and tell me what happens.

09:32.000 --> 09:34.000
Don't say that, Josephine.

09:34.000 --> 09:36.000
She's too old to wear that.

09:36.000 --> 09:38.000
I like it.

09:38.000 --> 09:41.000
I hope the young men on the beach like it too.

09:41.000 --> 09:45.000
Oh, dear Mother, you get worse as you get older.

09:45.000 --> 09:47.000
Please go and finish your packing.

09:47.000 --> 09:49.000
We're all ready late.

09:49.000 --> 09:51.000
Pete gets angry if we're late.

09:51.000 --> 09:53.000
Yes, dear, yes, dear.

09:53.000 --> 09:56.000
Just a few more things to pack.

09:56.000 --> 10:00.000
Oh, this tender thing is a bit uncomfortable.

10:00.000 --> 10:03.000
Does it look all right from behind?

10:03.000 --> 10:04.000
No, it doesn't.

10:04.000 --> 10:05.000
Oh, it looks fun.

10:05.000 --> 10:08.000
Fantastic, grand.

10:08.000 --> 10:11.000
Go and ask Dad what he thinks.

10:11.000 --> 10:14.000
That's a good idea.

10:14.000 --> 10:15.000
He's a man.

10:15.000 --> 10:17.000
No, it's not a good idea, Mum.

10:17.000 --> 10:19.000
Josephine is joking.

10:29.000 --> 10:32.000
Pete, come into the house, please.

10:32.000 --> 10:34.000
Our suitcases are ready.

10:34.000 --> 10:37.000
I think my mother is ready too.

10:37.000 --> 10:39.000
Okay, the car's ready.

10:39.000 --> 10:42.000
The engine sounds fantastic.

10:42.000 --> 10:44.000
No problems.

10:46.000 --> 10:48.000
I'm not so sure.

10:48.000 --> 10:51.000
It's my mother, Rick, with her bag.

10:51.000 --> 10:52.000
Yes?

10:52.000 --> 10:54.000
So she is coming with us.

10:54.000 --> 10:56.000
Of course she is.

10:56.000 --> 10:59.000
Super terrific, fantastic.

10:59.000 --> 11:02.000
I am so happy.

11:16.000 --> 11:24.000
Can I come in?

11:24.000 --> 11:25.000
Are you ready?

11:25.000 --> 11:27.000
I want to take your bag.

11:27.000 --> 11:29.000
You want to take me back?

11:29.000 --> 11:31.000
No, don't.

11:31.000 --> 11:33.000
I don't want to go back there.

11:33.000 --> 11:34.000
Not there.

11:34.000 --> 11:36.000
Nancy said I can stay here.

11:36.000 --> 11:37.000
What?

11:37.000 --> 11:38.000
What are you talking about?

11:38.000 --> 11:39.000
Nancy, stop him.

11:39.000 --> 11:41.000
He wants to take me back.

11:41.000 --> 11:43.000
I don't know what you're talking about.

11:43.000 --> 11:45.000
Please stay, don't send me back.

11:45.000 --> 11:46.000
Shut up, please.

11:46.000 --> 11:51.000
All I said was that I want to take your B-A-G bag.

11:51.000 --> 11:52.000
Bag!

11:52.000 --> 11:54.000
What's the problem now?

11:54.000 --> 11:56.000
He wants to take me back.

11:56.000 --> 11:57.000
He doesn't like me.

11:57.000 --> 11:59.000
Why did you say that, Pete?

11:59.000 --> 12:02.000
Why did you always upset my mother?

12:02.000 --> 12:06.000
All I said to the old fossil was that I want to take her bag.

12:06.000 --> 12:07.000
Bag!

12:07.000 --> 12:10.000
I am not an old fossil.

12:10.000 --> 12:15.000
Robert, a friend at the Bingo Club said I look like Marilyn Monroe.

12:15.000 --> 12:17.000
Robert thinks everyone looks like her.

12:17.000 --> 12:19.000
Last week he called me, Marilyn.

12:19.000 --> 12:21.000
Stop it, both of you.

12:21.000 --> 12:25.000
Take her suitcase, Pete, and then collect Joses.

12:25.000 --> 12:27.000
What is in this suitcase?

12:27.000 --> 12:29.000
It's so heavy.

12:29.000 --> 12:31.000
Are you stealing our silver?

12:31.000 --> 12:33.000
Don't start again, Pete.

12:33.000 --> 12:34.000
I'm going.

12:34.000 --> 12:36.000
I'm going.

12:40.000 --> 12:42.000
It's too loud.

12:42.000 --> 12:44.000
Stop playing now, Josephine.

12:44.000 --> 12:46.000
Turn it down.

12:46.000 --> 12:48.000
What a noise.

12:48.000 --> 12:50.000
Stop playing.

12:50.000 --> 12:52.000
What do you say, Dad?

12:52.000 --> 12:54.000
I said, turn it down.

12:54.000 --> 12:56.000
Oh.

12:56.000 --> 12:57.000
You have.

12:57.000 --> 13:00.000
Why do you play that terrible music, Josephine?

13:00.000 --> 13:02.000
I think it's great.

13:02.000 --> 13:05.000
It's what I want to do to write music.

13:05.000 --> 13:08.000
You think you can make a living with that kind of music?

13:08.000 --> 13:10.000
Well, I was young.

13:10.000 --> 13:12.000
They knew how to write music.

13:12.000 --> 13:14.000
And the words were important.

13:14.000 --> 13:15.000
And now...

13:15.000 --> 13:16.000
Yes, Dad.

13:16.000 --> 13:17.000
I know.

13:17.000 --> 13:18.000
You tell me every day.

13:18.000 --> 13:19.000
When you get older.

13:19.000 --> 13:20.000
Oh, yes.

13:20.000 --> 13:21.000
Same old story.

13:21.000 --> 13:22.000
Shut up.

13:22.000 --> 13:24.000
I'm not interested.

13:24.000 --> 13:27.000
I don't want any arguments on holiday.

13:27.000 --> 13:30.000
This is the only time your mother and I can relax.

13:30.000 --> 13:33.000
I don't want any problems, Josephine.

13:33.000 --> 13:36.000
Come with me and bring your suitcase to the car now.

13:36.000 --> 13:37.000
Now.

13:37.000 --> 13:39.000
Naff, Blackpool.

13:39.000 --> 13:41.000
Boring family.

13:41.000 --> 13:42.000
Boring life.

13:42.000 --> 13:43.000
I hate it.

13:49.000 --> 13:50.000
Hurry up, Nancy.

13:50.000 --> 13:51.000
Get in the car.

13:51.000 --> 13:52.000
We're waiting.

13:52.000 --> 13:53.000
Just wait a minute, dear.

13:53.000 --> 13:55.000
Graham isn't here.

13:55.000 --> 13:58.000
You don't want to go without her, do you?

13:58.000 --> 14:00.000
I said you don't want to go without her.

14:00.000 --> 14:01.000
I heard you.

14:01.000 --> 14:02.000
No.

14:02.000 --> 14:04.000
I don't want to go without her.

14:04.000 --> 14:06.000
But perhaps we could try it.

14:06.000 --> 14:09.000
Be honest to a dear for once in your life.

14:09.000 --> 14:12.000
We're all the family she has now.

14:12.000 --> 14:13.000
Yes, dear.

14:13.000 --> 14:15.000
But where is she?

14:15.000 --> 14:17.000
Get off, Boris.

14:17.000 --> 14:18.000
Stop it.

14:18.000 --> 14:20.000
Don't get Morris excited.

14:20.000 --> 14:23.000
You know what happens if he gets too excited.

14:23.000 --> 14:24.000
Stop it, Morris.

14:24.000 --> 14:26.000
Don't do that.

14:26.000 --> 14:27.000
Oh.

14:27.000 --> 14:28.000
No.

14:28.000 --> 14:30.000
What's wrong, Pete?

14:30.000 --> 14:33.000
What's that smell?

14:33.000 --> 14:35.000
Why do we keep this dog?

14:35.000 --> 14:36.000
Get off me.

14:36.000 --> 14:38.000
Look what he's done.

14:38.000 --> 14:39.000
Oh.

14:39.000 --> 14:42.000
Now I have to change my shirt.

14:42.000 --> 14:44.000
What a family.

14:44.000 --> 14:47.000
Wonderful start to the holiday.

14:47.000 --> 14:48.000
Why?

14:48.000 --> 14:49.000
Oh, what?

14:49.000 --> 14:52.000
Boris was sick on Dad's shirt.

14:52.000 --> 14:54.000
It's not funny, Jessica.

14:56.000 --> 14:58.000
Boris, come here. Sit quietly.

14:58.000 --> 15:00.000
You're a bad dog.

15:00.000 --> 15:01.000
Here I am.

15:04.000 --> 15:06.000
Oh.

15:06.000 --> 15:08.000
Where's your husband Nancy?

15:08.000 --> 15:10.000
He's always late.

15:10.000 --> 15:11.000
Oh.

15:11.000 --> 15:13.000
What's that smell?

15:13.000 --> 15:14.000
Is it Pete?

15:14.000 --> 15:15.000
It smells.

15:15.000 --> 15:16.000
Yes, Mother.

15:16.000 --> 15:17.000
Thank you.

15:17.000 --> 15:19.000
Boris was sick on Pete.

15:19.000 --> 15:21.000
He's changing his shirt.

15:21.000 --> 15:23.000
I don't know why you married him, Nancy.

15:23.000 --> 15:26.000
What's that noise?

15:26.000 --> 15:30.000
Have you got that rat with you, Josephine?

15:31.000 --> 15:32.000
Oh, no.

15:32.000 --> 15:34.000
Your father told you not to bring it.

15:34.000 --> 15:36.000
I know, Mum.

15:36.000 --> 15:39.000
But I want Robbie to come on a holiday.

15:39.000 --> 15:41.000
He's very quiet.

15:41.000 --> 15:43.000
Please don't tell Dad.

15:43.000 --> 15:44.000
Please.

15:44.000 --> 15:45.000
I like him.

15:45.000 --> 15:46.000
He's sweet.

15:46.000 --> 15:47.000
Please, Mum.

15:47.000 --> 15:49.000
Promise not to say anything.

15:49.000 --> 15:50.000
Please.

15:50.000 --> 15:52.000
I'm not happy, Josephine.

15:52.000 --> 15:54.000
Your father said no.

15:54.000 --> 15:57.000
When he finds out that you have that rat with you.

15:57.000 --> 15:59.000
I hate pets.

15:59.000 --> 16:01.000
Why do we keep it?

16:01.000 --> 16:02.000
I like him.

16:02.000 --> 16:03.000
He's sweet.

16:03.000 --> 16:06.000
It's loud and too expensive.

16:06.000 --> 16:09.000
I don't know what you mean.

16:09.000 --> 16:13.000
He's always very quiet and he costs nothing to feed.

16:13.000 --> 16:18.000
Josephine, show him what are you talking about, Gran.

16:18.000 --> 16:20.000
You gave it a jam sandwich at the breakfast table.

16:20.000 --> 16:23.000
I didn't feed him at the breakfast table.

16:23.000 --> 16:24.000
Yes, you did.

16:24.000 --> 16:25.000
I saw you.

16:25.000 --> 16:27.000
You fed it a strawberry sandwich.

16:27.000 --> 16:29.000
No, I didn't.

16:29.000 --> 16:31.000
Please tell him Nancy.

16:31.000 --> 16:33.000
Don't ask Nancy.

16:33.000 --> 16:35.000
I think your mother is losing her memory.

16:35.000 --> 16:38.000
Perhaps an old people's home is the place for her now.

16:38.000 --> 16:40.000
He doesn't like me, Nancy.

16:40.000 --> 16:43.000
He wants to put me into a home.

16:43.000 --> 16:45.000
I always knew he didn't like me.

16:45.000 --> 16:47.000
Both of you be quiet.

16:47.000 --> 16:50.000
I'm getting one of my headaches.

16:50.000 --> 16:54.000
I just want a few days of relaxation.

16:54.000 --> 16:56.000
Everyone be quiet.

16:56.000 --> 16:59.000
It wasn't my fault, wasn't it?

16:59.000 --> 17:02.000
You can't wear that t-shirt, dear.

17:02.000 --> 17:06.000
It's too small and I can see your stomach.

17:06.000 --> 17:08.000
It looks good.

17:08.000 --> 17:10.000
I always wear it on holiday.

17:10.000 --> 17:13.000
I know, dear, but it's very old.

17:13.000 --> 17:15.000
You have other new t-shirts.

17:15.000 --> 17:18.000
I know, but this is my favourite.

17:18.000 --> 17:23.000
Do you think a t-shirt with a picture of Cliff Richard on it is alright?

17:23.000 --> 17:27.000
We are staying at the Grand Park Hotel.

17:27.000 --> 17:30.000
I don't think it's a good idea.

17:30.000 --> 17:32.000
It's my holiday as well.

17:32.000 --> 17:34.000
I think it's great.

17:34.000 --> 17:36.000
I like Cliff Richard.

17:36.000 --> 17:38.000
He's a nice man.

17:38.000 --> 17:42.000
Why didn't you marry someone like Cliff Richard, Nancy?

17:42.000 --> 17:46.000
He's got a lovely smile and lovely teeth.

17:46.000 --> 17:50.000
Oh, a summer holiday, summer holiday.

17:50.000 --> 17:54.000
One day some, one day some, one day.

18:00.000 --> 18:03.000
Is this car okay?

18:03.000 --> 18:05.000
Of course, no problems.

18:07.000 --> 18:09.000
Are we ready now? Can we go?

18:09.000 --> 18:12.000
Wait a minute, I must go to the toilet again.

18:12.000 --> 18:14.000
Just wait a minute please.

18:16.000 --> 18:17.000
Oh no.

18:18.000 --> 18:21.000
I don't want to stop every ten minutes for your mother.

18:21.000 --> 18:25.000
Nancy, we have 250 miles to drive today.

18:25.000 --> 18:28.000
I hope this piece of junk can go 250 miles.

18:28.000 --> 18:31.000
No problem, trust me.

18:31.000 --> 18:34.000
Sometimes I think you don't trust me dear.

18:34.000 --> 18:39.000
No, you're right. I don't trust you.

18:43.000 --> 18:46.000
I'm okay. We can go.

18:47.000 --> 18:49.000
Last, last, last, last.

18:49.000 --> 18:51.000
APPLAUSE

19:12.000 --> 19:17.000
12 hours to drive 250 miles.

19:17.000 --> 19:20.000
It's now nearly midnight.

19:20.000 --> 19:23.000
I'm hungry. I want a burger.

19:23.000 --> 19:26.000
Oh, that's a good idea, Josie.

19:26.000 --> 19:28.000
I want one too.

19:28.000 --> 19:32.000
What a terrible journey. It was worse than last year.

19:32.000 --> 19:33.000
Yes, but...

19:33.000 --> 19:36.000
This is the last holiday we come in that car.

19:36.000 --> 19:37.000
Yes.

19:37.000 --> 19:42.000
I am not coming to Blackpool again in a car that breaks down every 20 miles.

19:42.000 --> 19:43.000
Yes.

19:43.000 --> 19:45.000
I'm hungry. I want a burger.

19:45.000 --> 19:48.000
With chips and lots of tomato ketchup.

19:48.000 --> 19:50.000
How are you trying to say, Pete?

19:50.000 --> 19:53.000
Yes, but nothing, dear.

19:53.000 --> 19:55.000
I want a new car.

19:55.000 --> 19:56.000
Yes.

19:56.000 --> 19:58.000
All my friends laugh when they see us in that car.

19:58.000 --> 20:00.000
It's quicker by bike.

20:00.000 --> 20:02.000
And a medium collar.

20:02.000 --> 20:05.000
No, a large one. I am on holiday.

20:05.000 --> 20:08.000
Yes, but it is a classic car.

20:08.000 --> 20:10.000
What's wrong with it?

20:10.000 --> 20:17.000
It is old, unreliable, uncomfortable, noisy, smelly, expensive.

20:17.000 --> 20:20.000
I hate the color. I hate it.

20:20.000 --> 20:22.000
Do you understand?

20:22.000 --> 20:24.000
So, you don't like it, dear?

20:24.000 --> 20:27.000
No. I don't like it.

20:27.000 --> 20:29.000
Do you ever listen to me?

20:29.000 --> 20:30.000
Sorry?

20:30.000 --> 20:31.000
I don't.

20:31.000 --> 20:33.000
I'm hungry. I want a burger.

20:33.000 --> 20:35.000
You're quiet, Josie. Not now.

20:35.000 --> 20:38.000
We can buy you a burger as well, Nancy.

20:38.000 --> 20:40.000
Thank you, Mum.

20:40.000 --> 20:43.000
Burgers are not healthy. I'm on a diet.

20:43.000 --> 20:48.000
You're always on a diet. You still look fat.

20:48.000 --> 20:51.000
Come here, Boris. Come here. Don't do that.

20:51.000 --> 20:53.000
No. Catch him.

20:53.000 --> 20:55.000
Why did you let him go?

20:55.000 --> 20:59.000
I didn't let him go. He escaped through the car window.

20:59.000 --> 21:03.000
He's run onto the beach. I can hear him jumping in the waves.

21:03.000 --> 21:05.000
You can go and get him, Pete.

21:05.000 --> 21:07.000
Yes, dear. But why me?

21:07.000 --> 21:10.000
You are the man of the family, aren't you?

21:10.000 --> 21:12.000
Sometimes I'm not so sure.

21:12.000 --> 21:14.000
What do you mean, Nancy?

21:14.000 --> 21:18.000
Nothing, dear. I suppose it happens when you get older.

21:18.000 --> 21:19.000
What happened?

21:19.000 --> 21:23.000
Nothing. Anyway, what about Boris?

21:23.000 --> 21:26.000
We can talk later.

21:26.000 --> 21:30.000
Josephine? Nancy? Gran? Can you come and help me?

21:30.000 --> 21:33.000
Thank you, everyone.

21:33.000 --> 21:36.000
Wonderful, all family.

21:36.000 --> 21:39.000
I'm hungry. I want a burger.

21:39.000 --> 21:42.000
With chips and lots of tomato ketchup.

21:42.000 --> 21:47.000
It's nearly midnight, and all you two can think about is a burger.

21:47.000 --> 21:51.000
The burger shop is over there. I can see it. Five minutes and we're back.

21:51.000 --> 21:54.000
Come on, Gran. We're going.

21:54.000 --> 21:56.000
Have you got some money, Gran?

21:56.000 --> 22:01.000
Yes, but I want a double portion of chips and lots of tomato ketchup.

22:01.000 --> 22:05.000
No problem, Gran. If you're paying.

22:05.000 --> 22:07.000
You can have what you want.

22:07.000 --> 22:09.000
Josephine?

22:09.000 --> 22:13.000
I want two burgers. I'm so hungry. I could eat Boris.

22:13.000 --> 22:14.000
One.

22:14.000 --> 22:18.000
Perhaps I can have a small burger as well.

22:18.000 --> 22:20.000
It is my holiday.

22:20.000 --> 22:22.000
One burger won't hurt my diet.

22:22.000 --> 22:24.000
But I don't want any chips and ketchup.

22:24.000 --> 22:27.000
Well done, Nancy. You only live once.

22:27.000 --> 22:29.000
It's about five minutes, Mum.

22:29.000 --> 22:32.000
Come on, Gran. Ooh, not so fast.

22:32.000 --> 22:35.000
You know I have a bad leg.

22:35.000 --> 22:38.000
It's Dad's birthday on Wednesday.

22:38.000 --> 22:40.000
Do you have a present for him?

22:40.000 --> 22:41.000
No.

22:41.000 --> 22:42.000
Do you?

22:42.000 --> 22:43.000
No.

22:43.000 --> 22:46.000
I never know what to buy him.

22:46.000 --> 22:48.000
I can't be bothered.

22:48.000 --> 22:52.000
Mum always buys something for me to give him. It's easier.

22:52.000 --> 22:54.000
Dad doesn't know.

22:54.000 --> 22:56.000
Nancy does the same for me.

22:56.000 --> 22:59.000
I never know what to get your father either.

23:00.000 --> 23:03.000
Oh, but what can we do for him this year?

23:03.000 --> 23:05.000
Something a bit different.

23:05.000 --> 23:07.000
And a bit shocking.

23:07.000 --> 23:10.000
What about a new Cliff Richard T-shirt?

23:10.000 --> 23:11.000
Oh.

23:11.000 --> 23:12.000
It's Naph.

23:12.000 --> 23:15.000
What about a stripper?

23:15.000 --> 23:18.000
Cool idea.

23:18.000 --> 23:21.000
But aren't they expensive?

23:21.000 --> 23:23.000
I wonder what Mum thinks.

23:23.000 --> 23:25.000
Don't tell your Mum.

23:25.000 --> 23:28.000
It's a surprise for both of them.

23:28.000 --> 23:31.000
Don't worry about the money I have enough with me.

23:31.000 --> 23:34.000
That's cool.

23:34.000 --> 23:35.000
What type of stripper?

23:35.000 --> 23:37.000
Leave it to me, Josie.

23:37.000 --> 23:38.000
Leave it to me.

23:38.000 --> 23:40.000
Oh, great. Well done, Gran.

23:40.000 --> 23:42.000
Oh, here we are.

23:42.000 --> 23:45.000
Now, don't forget, I want a double burger.

23:45.000 --> 23:49.000
No, a double cheese burger with extra chips.

23:49.000 --> 23:53.000
Oh, and do you think your Dad wants a burger as well?

23:53.000 --> 23:55.000
Don't waste your money.

23:55.000 --> 23:58.000
Save it to the stripper.

24:00.000 --> 24:03.000
Anyway, I think he's too busy at the moment,

24:03.000 --> 24:06.000
chasing Boris through the waves.

24:13.000 --> 24:16.000
Where is that, Doc? I can't find him.

24:16.000 --> 24:19.000
We're not waiting in this car any longer, Pete.

24:19.000 --> 24:22.000
It's getting cold and I want my bed.

24:23.000 --> 24:26.000
So come on, get the luggage and we can check in.

24:26.000 --> 24:30.000
Okay. Okay, I can look for him later, I suppose.

24:30.000 --> 24:32.000
What a day.

24:32.000 --> 24:36.000
You can look for him if you want. I'm tired.

24:36.000 --> 24:38.000
What's that smell?

24:38.000 --> 24:40.000
What are you eating, Josie?

24:40.000 --> 24:42.000
A burger.

24:42.000 --> 24:46.000
You too, Gran, and Nancy, you are all eating.

24:46.000 --> 24:49.000
Where is my burger? I'm so hungry.

24:49.000 --> 24:52.000
Sorry, we forgot to get you one.

24:52.000 --> 24:54.000
You didn't say you wanted a burger.

24:54.000 --> 24:57.000
That's because I wasn't here.

24:57.000 --> 25:00.000
I was running up and down the beach in the dark,

25:00.000 --> 25:02.000
looking for that stupid dog.

25:02.000 --> 25:04.000
I fell over twice.

25:04.000 --> 25:06.000
The couples were very angry.

25:06.000 --> 25:08.000
It was embarrassing.

25:08.000 --> 25:11.000
They were, um, busy.

25:14.000 --> 25:16.000
Oh, wait a minute.

25:16.000 --> 25:19.000
A biscuit at the bottom of my handbag.

25:19.000 --> 25:21.000
Um, oh, yes, here it is.

25:21.000 --> 25:24.000
Oh, thank you very much.

25:24.000 --> 25:26.000
Nice of you to think of me.

25:26.000 --> 25:28.000
Oh, how wonderful.

25:28.000 --> 25:29.000
One biscuit.

25:29.000 --> 25:31.000
Not even a chocolate biscuit.

25:31.000 --> 25:34.000
Just a plain, boring, tasteless biscuit.

25:34.000 --> 25:37.000
I hope I can sleep tonight on such a full stomach.

25:37.000 --> 25:40.000
There's no need to be so sarcastic.

25:40.000 --> 25:43.000
Oh, it tastes terrible.

25:43.000 --> 25:44.000
What is it?

25:44.000 --> 25:46.000
Maybe to me, Pete.

25:46.000 --> 25:48.000
Now, where are my glasses?

25:48.000 --> 25:50.000
Oh, I can't find them.

25:50.000 --> 25:53.000
What does it say on the packet, Nancy?

25:53.000 --> 25:56.000
Wonderful, woofy biscuits.

25:56.000 --> 25:58.000
It's a dog biscuit.

25:58.000 --> 26:00.000
A dog biscuit?

26:00.000 --> 26:02.000
I ate a dog biscuit.

26:02.000 --> 26:05.000
I think I need a doctor.

26:05.000 --> 26:06.000
I suddenly feel real.

26:06.000 --> 26:07.000
Oh, don't worry.

26:07.000 --> 26:08.000
It's OK.

26:08.000 --> 26:11.000
When you start barking, I can ask for a doctor.

26:12.000 --> 26:13.000
Come on.

26:13.000 --> 26:15.000
Let's go into the hotel.

26:23.000 --> 26:27.000
Oh, good evening, Mr. and Mrs. Britain and family.

26:27.000 --> 26:30.000
Oh, hello, Mr. Bertolini.

26:30.000 --> 26:32.000
Luigi.

26:32.000 --> 26:34.000
Lovely to see you again.

26:34.000 --> 26:35.000
How are you?

26:35.000 --> 26:37.000
I'm fine.

26:37.000 --> 26:38.000
And you?

26:38.000 --> 26:40.000
Oh, we're all fine.

26:40.000 --> 26:41.000
Thank you.

26:41.000 --> 26:45.000
It's so nice to be here in your lovely hotel.

26:45.000 --> 26:49.000
You are looking younger than last year, Nancy.

26:49.000 --> 26:51.000
Do you think so?

26:51.000 --> 26:54.000
Oh, thank you so much.

26:54.000 --> 26:59.000
I made a reservation for two double rooms with a bathroom for one week.

26:59.000 --> 27:02.000
Eh, but I don't understand.

27:02.000 --> 27:04.000
You are one week early?

27:04.000 --> 27:07.000
You have a booking from next Saturday, not today.

27:07.000 --> 27:09.000
No, that is wrong.

27:09.000 --> 27:13.000
I phoned two months ago and booked seven nights for this week.

27:13.000 --> 27:15.000
No, I'm sorry, Mr. Britain.

27:15.000 --> 27:20.000
I answered the phone myself and I put it into the computer system immediately.

27:20.000 --> 27:21.000
Oh, no.

27:21.000 --> 27:23.000
I can't believe it.

27:23.000 --> 27:24.000
There must be some escape.

27:24.000 --> 27:26.000
I hope so.

27:26.000 --> 27:29.000
I am not going home at this time.

27:29.000 --> 27:32.000
I'm sure it isn't a problem, is it?

27:32.000 --> 27:34.000
Eh, let me see.

27:34.000 --> 27:38.000
I am sorry, but we only have one spare room at the moment.

27:38.000 --> 27:40.000
We are almost fully booked tonight.

27:40.000 --> 27:42.000
We have a wedding party.

27:42.000 --> 27:43.000
That's okay.

27:43.000 --> 27:46.000
My wife and daughter and I can have the one room.

27:46.000 --> 27:50.000
My wife's mother can sleep on some chairs in the hotel bar.

27:50.000 --> 27:54.000
Look, if she gets thirsty in the night, she can have a drink or two.

27:54.000 --> 27:55.000
My side?

27:55.000 --> 27:57.000
Don't you think, Graham?

27:57.000 --> 27:58.000
Makes you happy?

27:58.000 --> 27:59.000
Stop it, Peter.

27:59.000 --> 28:01.000
Mum is not sleeping in the bar.

28:01.000 --> 28:03.000
I am not sleeping in the bar.

28:03.000 --> 28:07.000
I have a bad back, and my plumbing is not so good.

28:07.000 --> 28:09.000
Mum is only joking.

28:09.000 --> 28:11.000
There is a bed for you.

28:11.000 --> 28:13.000
Of course I was only joking.

28:13.000 --> 28:16.000
Maybe you have a cupboard somewhere in the cellar?

28:16.000 --> 28:17.000
No.

28:17.000 --> 28:19.000
Mum is in the room with Josie and myself.

28:19.000 --> 28:22.000
You, Pete, can find somewhere else to sleep.

28:22.000 --> 28:23.000
What?

28:23.000 --> 28:24.000
No!

28:24.000 --> 28:27.000
It was your job to book the hotel.

28:27.000 --> 28:30.000
I can't get you to do a simple job like that.

28:30.000 --> 28:33.000
You made the mistake, so it's your problem.

28:33.000 --> 28:35.000
Where do I go?

28:35.000 --> 28:37.000
You can find another hotel.

28:37.000 --> 28:38.000
You can sleep on the beach.

28:38.000 --> 28:40.000
You can sleep in your wonderful car.

28:40.000 --> 28:41.000
I don't care.

28:41.000 --> 28:42.000
Good night.

28:42.000 --> 28:44.000
Luigi.

28:44.000 --> 28:47.000
Can you take me to our room, please?

28:47.000 --> 28:49.000
Of course, Nancy.

28:49.000 --> 28:51.000
This way, please.

28:51.000 --> 28:53.000
It's a nice room.

28:53.000 --> 28:55.000
Very comfortable beds.

28:55.000 --> 28:58.000
That sounds very nice.

28:58.000 --> 29:00.000
Come this way, please.

29:00.000 --> 29:02.000
We are back, Josephine.

29:02.000 --> 29:04.000
Mum, come on.

29:04.000 --> 29:05.000
But...

29:05.000 --> 29:06.000
Good night, Dad.

29:06.000 --> 29:08.000
Sleep well.

29:08.000 --> 29:10.000
Sweet dreams.

29:10.000 --> 29:11.000
But...

29:24.000 --> 29:26.000
I can't believe it.

29:26.000 --> 29:28.000
Where were you, Boris?

29:28.000 --> 29:29.000
Come here.

29:30.000 --> 29:32.000
Be quiet.

29:32.000 --> 29:35.000
Don't wake up the guests of the hotel.

29:35.000 --> 29:38.000
Be quiet.

29:38.000 --> 29:39.000
Come on.

29:39.000 --> 29:40.000
Get in the car.

29:45.000 --> 29:47.000
Just lay down, Doc.

29:47.000 --> 29:48.000
Be quiet.

29:48.000 --> 29:50.000
I don't believe it.

29:50.000 --> 29:52.000
The first night of the holiday,

29:52.000 --> 29:55.000
and I'm sleeping in the car with you.

29:55.000 --> 29:57.000
Stop barking.

29:57.000 --> 30:01.000
Can we try to sleep now, please, Boris?

30:01.000 --> 30:05.000
I am very, very tired.

30:05.000 --> 30:08.000
What's that noise?

30:08.000 --> 30:09.000
Go away.

30:09.000 --> 30:11.000
Be quiet, Doc.

30:11.000 --> 30:13.000
I'm going mad.

30:13.000 --> 30:16.000
Please open your window, sir.

30:16.000 --> 30:17.000
What?

30:17.000 --> 30:19.000
Oh, no.

30:19.000 --> 30:20.000
The police.

30:20.000 --> 30:21.000
What?

30:21.000 --> 30:24.000
Please open your window, sir.

30:24.000 --> 30:25.000
Yes, sir.

30:25.000 --> 30:28.000
Get off, Boris.

30:29.000 --> 30:32.000
No, Boris, not there.

30:32.000 --> 30:36.000
Open your window now, please, sir.

30:36.000 --> 30:38.000
Yes, officer.

30:38.000 --> 30:39.000
Doc!

30:39.000 --> 30:41.000
Wait a minute.

30:41.000 --> 30:42.000
Boris.

30:42.000 --> 30:45.000
What is the problem, sir?

30:45.000 --> 30:46.000
Nothing, officer.

30:46.000 --> 30:49.000
I just have a problem with the Doc, and, sir.

30:49.000 --> 30:52.000
Why are you sleeping in the car, sir?

30:52.000 --> 30:54.000
It's a long story.

30:54.000 --> 30:56.000
Get off, Boris.

30:56.000 --> 30:58.000
It worked.

30:58.000 --> 31:00.000
Well, officer.

31:00.000 --> 31:01.000
Yes, sir.

31:01.000 --> 31:05.000
Well, I said my wife's mother could sleep in the bar

31:05.000 --> 31:08.000
because she likes a drink or two,

31:08.000 --> 31:12.000
and you have a drink as well, sir.

31:12.000 --> 31:14.000
No, why?

31:14.000 --> 31:17.000
You are a little confused, sir.

31:17.000 --> 31:19.000
No, officer.

31:19.000 --> 31:21.000
It's all very simple.

31:21.000 --> 31:24.000
So, what are you doing now, sir?

31:24.000 --> 31:27.000
I'm staying here in the car for tonight,

31:27.000 --> 31:30.000
and I'm looking for another room in the morning.

31:30.000 --> 31:32.000
You can't park here, sir.

31:32.000 --> 31:36.000
This is a private car park for hotel guests only.

31:36.000 --> 31:39.000
I am a guest at this hotel.

31:39.000 --> 31:40.000
Oh.

31:40.000 --> 31:45.000
That's why you're sleeping in the hotel car park, is it, sir?

31:45.000 --> 31:46.000
Hmm.

31:46.000 --> 31:49.000
It does sound a little strange, officer,

31:49.000 --> 31:52.000
but there is a simple explanation.

31:52.000 --> 31:53.000
Yes, sir.

31:53.000 --> 31:55.000
Of course there is, sir.

31:55.000 --> 31:58.000
I can see you don't believe me.

31:58.000 --> 32:01.000
What makes you think that, sir?

32:01.000 --> 32:05.000
You have one minute to explain to me why you're in this car

32:05.000 --> 32:08.000
with a man barking dog.

32:08.000 --> 32:12.000
Well, it all started when I booked the hotel.

32:12.000 --> 32:16.000
The Italian manager said I booked for next week,

32:16.000 --> 32:19.000
but I know I booked for this week.

32:20.000 --> 32:22.000
That's the problem with foreigners.

32:22.000 --> 32:24.000
They don't understand English.

32:24.000 --> 32:27.000
Even when you shout at them, they don't understand.

32:27.000 --> 32:30.000
Is this important for your story, sir?

32:30.000 --> 32:33.000
Well, er, yes and no.

32:33.000 --> 32:38.000
Anyway, I thought I could sleep with the two women in one room

32:38.000 --> 32:41.000
and the mother-in-law could sleep in the bar.

32:41.000 --> 32:42.000
That's enough, sir.

32:42.000 --> 32:45.000
Can you move your car, sir, now?

32:45.000 --> 32:47.000
But where to?

32:47.000 --> 32:49.000
Perhaps you could drive home, sir.

32:49.000 --> 32:52.000
That's 250 miles.

32:52.000 --> 32:57.000
Well, you can't stay here and you can't stay on the seafront.

32:57.000 --> 32:59.000
There's a carport behind the shopping centre,

32:59.000 --> 33:03.000
but I think that's closed at this time of night.

33:03.000 --> 33:06.000
I'm sorry, officer, but I'm staying here.

33:06.000 --> 33:09.000
That's final. I am tired.

33:09.000 --> 33:13.000
The day was terrible. I am staying here.

33:14.000 --> 33:17.000
That is not a good decision, sir.

33:17.000 --> 33:19.000
Why not?

33:19.000 --> 33:23.000
I think the best idea is that you come to the police station

33:23.000 --> 33:27.000
and then we can have a chat and sort things out there.

33:27.000 --> 33:30.000
You can bring your beast with you as well, sir.

33:30.000 --> 33:33.000
You are joking, officer, aren't you?

33:33.000 --> 33:35.000
No, I'm not.

33:35.000 --> 33:37.000
Shut up!

33:37.000 --> 33:39.000
Are you talking to me, sir?

33:39.000 --> 33:41.000
No, of course not.

33:42.000 --> 33:45.000
Come on, sir. My car is over there.

33:45.000 --> 33:47.000
You can't do this.

33:47.000 --> 33:49.000
I am not a criminal.

33:49.000 --> 33:51.000
I can't believe it.

33:51.000 --> 33:53.000
It's your fault, Boris.

33:53.000 --> 33:55.000
For a holiday.

33:55.000 --> 33:57.000
What a life.

34:12.000 --> 34:15.000
I wonder where Peter's at the moment.

34:15.000 --> 34:17.000
I hope he's OK.

34:17.000 --> 34:19.000
Don't worry about him, Nancy.

34:19.000 --> 34:21.000
I'm sure he has a bed somewhere.

34:21.000 --> 34:25.000
I think I was a bit unkind to him this evening.

34:25.000 --> 34:27.000
Don't worry so much.

34:27.000 --> 34:30.000
I think I ate too many burgers.

34:30.000 --> 34:32.000
I feel a bit strange.

34:32.000 --> 34:34.000
And you ate two ice creams?

34:34.000 --> 34:35.000
Yes, I know.

34:35.000 --> 34:39.000
I never eat ice cream at home, but this is my holiday.

34:39.000 --> 34:43.000
Two ice creams, mum, really.

34:43.000 --> 34:47.000
I want to phone Pete to see if he's OK.

34:47.000 --> 34:49.000
Where's my mobile, Josie?

34:49.000 --> 34:50.000
I don't know.

34:50.000 --> 34:52.000
Why ask me?

34:52.000 --> 34:54.000
You're always losing it.

34:54.000 --> 34:57.000
Oh, no, I forgot about the rat.

34:57.000 --> 34:59.000
If your dad finds out, it's here with us.

34:59.000 --> 35:01.000
He won't find out.

35:01.000 --> 35:02.000
Don't tell him.

35:02.000 --> 35:04.000
It's not my problem, Josephine.

35:04.000 --> 35:06.000
You promised not to tell him.

35:06.000 --> 35:07.000
No, I didn't.

35:07.000 --> 35:09.000
Don't say anything, mum.

35:09.000 --> 35:11.000
That's enough, Josephine.

35:11.000 --> 35:15.000
But it is not sleeping in the same room as us.

35:15.000 --> 35:17.000
Robbie's very quiet.

35:17.000 --> 35:18.000
He's no problem.

35:18.000 --> 35:20.000
Just chill out a bit, mum.

35:20.000 --> 35:23.000
It's not staying in the bedroom.

35:23.000 --> 35:25.000
Put it on the balcony, Josephine.

35:25.000 --> 35:27.000
I can't sleep with it in the room.

35:27.000 --> 35:30.000
Bloody marvellous.

35:30.000 --> 35:32.000
Where is my mobile?

35:32.000 --> 35:34.000
Mum, do you know where it is?

35:34.000 --> 35:35.000
What, Nancy?

35:35.000 --> 35:38.000
Robbie is in Josie's pocket.

35:38.000 --> 35:40.000
No, no, my mobile.

35:40.000 --> 35:41.000
Mobile what?

35:41.000 --> 35:42.000
Telephone.

35:42.000 --> 35:43.000
Mobile.

35:43.000 --> 35:44.000
Telephone.

35:44.000 --> 35:46.000
You know the small telephone I have.

35:46.000 --> 35:49.000
There's a telephone by the side of the bed.

35:49.000 --> 35:54.000
No, I can't use that because I don't know where Pete is staying.

35:54.000 --> 35:55.000
With my mobile...

35:55.000 --> 35:57.000
Oh, it doesn't matter.

35:57.000 --> 36:00.000
Josie, I think it's in the car.

36:00.000 --> 36:02.000
Can you go down to the car, park and have a look?

36:02.000 --> 36:04.000
Oh, mum.

36:04.000 --> 36:05.000
Why me?

36:05.000 --> 36:07.000
Just do it, Josie, please.

36:07.000 --> 36:10.000
But, mum, I don't want to.

36:10.000 --> 36:12.000
You go.

36:12.000 --> 36:13.000
It's dark.

36:13.000 --> 36:15.000
We can go together, Josie.

36:15.000 --> 36:16.000
Come on.

36:16.000 --> 36:20.000
I think a little fresh air might be good for my stomach.

36:20.000 --> 36:23.000
I don't feel too good at the moment.

36:23.000 --> 36:26.000
Mum is super stressed at the moment, Grand.

36:26.000 --> 36:28.000
She really gets all my nerves.

36:28.000 --> 36:30.000
Don't worry, Josie.

36:30.000 --> 36:32.000
I'm sure it's nothing serious.

36:32.000 --> 36:33.000
But you are right.

36:33.000 --> 36:34.000
She is stressed.

36:34.000 --> 36:37.000
And sometimes she does strange things.

36:37.000 --> 36:39.000
Come here, you little thing.

36:39.000 --> 36:40.000
Oh.

36:40.000 --> 36:43.000
You don't want to sleep on that balcony tonight, do you?

36:43.000 --> 36:45.000
Oh, Robbie, can you?

36:45.000 --> 36:48.000
Oh, I don't want to sleep on that balcony tonight.

36:48.000 --> 36:51.000
I don't want to sleep on that balcony tonight, do you?

36:51.000 --> 36:54.000
Oh, Robbie can sleep in the car, in the car park.

36:54.000 --> 36:57.000
After breakfast, you can feed him.

36:57.000 --> 36:59.000
What do you think?

36:59.000 --> 37:03.000
Well, it's better than the balcony, I suppose.

37:03.000 --> 37:05.000
OK.

37:05.000 --> 37:07.000
Oh.

37:07.000 --> 37:10.000
Where is our car?

37:10.000 --> 37:12.000
They all look the same to me.

37:12.000 --> 37:14.000
It's easy to find our car.

37:14.000 --> 37:17.000
It's the only one that looks like it escaped from a museum.

37:18.000 --> 37:19.000
Oh, yes.

37:19.000 --> 37:21.000
There it is.

37:21.000 --> 37:23.000
The car's empty.

37:23.000 --> 37:28.000
I thought that perhaps Dad and Boris were cuddling up on the back seat together.

37:28.000 --> 37:30.000
Oh, shit.

37:30.000 --> 37:32.000
We must be quiet.

37:32.000 --> 37:34.000
It's late.

37:34.000 --> 37:38.000
Now, what is it we're looking for?

37:38.000 --> 37:41.000
Something called a no-bile, whatever that is.

37:41.000 --> 37:44.000
It's a Moby Gran.

37:44.000 --> 37:46.000
Don't you know what a Moby is?

37:46.000 --> 37:48.000
A Gran?

37:48.000 --> 37:50.000
A mobile?

37:50.000 --> 37:52.000
Everyone has one.

37:52.000 --> 37:55.000
Oh, I don't understand this modern technology.

37:55.000 --> 37:59.000
I liked it when people talked to each other and wrote letters.

37:59.000 --> 38:01.000
Oh, it sounds so old.

38:01.000 --> 38:02.000
Oh.

38:02.000 --> 38:04.000
Where is the Moby?

38:04.000 --> 38:07.000
Oh, I can't find it.

38:07.000 --> 38:09.000
It's not bloody here.

38:09.000 --> 38:10.000
Oh, dear.

38:10.000 --> 38:12.000
Come on, stupid mother.

38:12.000 --> 38:14.000
It must be in the bedroom.

38:14.000 --> 38:17.000
Don't forget to leave your little friend here.

38:17.000 --> 38:18.000
Oh, yes.

38:18.000 --> 38:20.000
Come on, Moby.

38:20.000 --> 38:23.000
You can sleep here on this coat.

38:23.000 --> 38:24.000
Okay.

38:24.000 --> 38:26.000
Sleep well.

38:26.000 --> 38:31.000
I'm sleeping by myself on the sofa in the bedroom.

38:31.000 --> 38:33.000
You and Mum can have the double bed, okay?

38:33.000 --> 38:35.000
That's fine.

38:35.000 --> 38:37.000
I have a bad bed.

38:37.000 --> 38:38.000
Yes, I know.

38:38.000 --> 38:42.000
I wonder which hotel Dad is sleeping in.

38:42.000 --> 38:44.000
Maybe he's not alone.

38:44.000 --> 38:46.000
He's got Boris with him.

38:46.000 --> 38:48.000
Oh, yes, I forgot.

38:48.000 --> 38:52.000
Oh, I don't have a key for the bedroom.

38:52.000 --> 38:54.000
Do you, Josie?

38:54.000 --> 38:57.000
No, but Mum is there, so don't get stressed.

38:57.000 --> 38:59.000
Try it again.

38:59.000 --> 39:02.000
Perhaps Nancy is in the bathroom.

39:02.000 --> 39:05.000
Strange?

39:05.000 --> 39:08.000
Mum, are you there?

39:08.000 --> 39:11.000
Open the sodding door.

39:11.000 --> 39:13.000
Is it the right room?

39:13.000 --> 39:15.000
They all look the same to me.

39:15.000 --> 39:17.000
Of course it's the right room.

39:17.000 --> 39:19.000
Mum, wake up.

39:19.000 --> 39:20.000
Open the bleeding door.

39:20.000 --> 39:21.000
Let us in.

39:25.000 --> 39:27.000
Oh, sorry.

39:27.000 --> 39:31.000
I, um, just, well, I went out for a minute.

39:31.000 --> 39:33.000
You're a cooker than I am.

39:33.000 --> 39:35.000
I was way longer than, um...

39:35.000 --> 39:38.000
You're all right, Nancy.

39:38.000 --> 39:40.000
You look a little hot and red.

39:40.000 --> 39:41.000
Were you running?

39:41.000 --> 39:42.000
No.

39:42.000 --> 39:43.000
Yes.

39:43.000 --> 39:44.000
Yes.

39:44.000 --> 39:46.000
I went for a jog in the hotel.

39:46.000 --> 39:48.000
I think it was the burger, too.

39:48.000 --> 39:53.000
I don't think a night dress is the right thing to wear for jogging, is it?

39:53.000 --> 39:55.000
It's very quiet in the hotel.

39:55.000 --> 39:57.000
No one saw us, Ernie.

39:57.000 --> 39:59.000
I can't find your Moby.

39:59.000 --> 40:01.000
I think it's lost.

40:01.000 --> 40:02.000
What's lost?

40:02.000 --> 40:04.000
Your mobile, Mum.

40:04.000 --> 40:05.000
My mobile?

40:05.000 --> 40:06.000
Oh, yes.

40:06.000 --> 40:08.000
How can I have it, please?

40:08.000 --> 40:10.000
I can't find it.

40:10.000 --> 40:11.000
I just told you.

40:11.000 --> 40:12.000
Okay.

40:12.000 --> 40:13.000
Right.

40:13.000 --> 40:14.000
Good.

40:14.000 --> 40:18.000
I think a good night's sleep is what we all need.

40:18.000 --> 40:20.000
Come on, Nancy.

40:20.000 --> 40:21.000
Open up the door.

40:21.000 --> 40:23.000
We don't have to stand in the corridor.

40:23.000 --> 40:25.000
Good idea, Mum.

40:25.000 --> 40:28.000
I'm in the bathroom first.

40:30.000 --> 40:33.000
Don't take too long, Josephine.

40:33.000 --> 40:34.000
Oh.

40:34.000 --> 40:35.000
Ah.

40:35.000 --> 40:36.000
Oh.

40:36.000 --> 40:37.000
Ah.

40:37.000 --> 40:38.000
Oh.

40:38.000 --> 40:39.000
Ah.

40:39.000 --> 40:40.000
Oh.

40:40.000 --> 40:42.000
What are you doing, Mum?

40:42.000 --> 40:46.000
I want to get my body in good shape.

40:46.000 --> 40:48.000
What is that?

40:48.000 --> 40:50.000
My fitness equipment.

40:50.000 --> 40:53.000
I brought it with me in my sleep case.

40:53.000 --> 40:56.000
This helps strengthen the lower muscles.

40:56.000 --> 40:59.000
I want to look good in my new string bikini.

40:59.000 --> 41:06.000
It's half past ten in the morning.

41:06.000 --> 41:14.000
Where is Pete?

41:14.000 --> 41:16.000
Where is my bikini?

41:16.000 --> 41:18.000
I can't find my sun cream, Mum.

41:18.000 --> 41:20.000
Where the hell is it?

41:20.000 --> 41:21.000
I don't know.

41:21.000 --> 41:23.000
Where is Pete?

41:23.000 --> 41:25.000
Why isn't he here?

41:25.000 --> 41:27.000
I want to go to the beach.

41:27.000 --> 41:28.000
Why is he so late?

41:28.000 --> 41:30.000
Where is my mobile?

41:30.000 --> 41:31.000
Here it is.

41:31.000 --> 41:32.000
My mobile?

41:32.000 --> 41:33.000
No.

41:33.000 --> 41:34.000
My bikini.

41:34.000 --> 41:36.000
Did you unpack the sun cream, Mum?

41:36.000 --> 41:37.000
Yes.

41:37.000 --> 41:38.000
It's in the bathroom.

41:38.000 --> 41:39.000
On the show.

41:39.000 --> 41:40.000
I'm ready for the beach.

41:40.000 --> 41:41.000
Come on.

41:41.000 --> 41:42.000
Let's go.

41:42.000 --> 41:43.000
No.

41:43.000 --> 41:44.000
Wait.

41:44.000 --> 41:46.000
I want to know where Pete is.

41:46.000 --> 41:48.000
Come in.

41:48.000 --> 41:53.000
Open the door, please.

41:53.000 --> 41:54.000
Pete.

41:54.000 --> 41:56.000
Why are you so late?

41:56.000 --> 41:58.000
It's half past ten.

41:58.000 --> 42:00.000
We had breakfast one hour ago.

42:00.000 --> 42:02.000
We're ready for the beach.

42:02.000 --> 42:03.000
The weather's lovely.

42:03.000 --> 42:05.000
Don't ask.

42:05.000 --> 42:07.000
Don't ask about my night.

42:07.000 --> 42:09.000
Did you find a nice hotel?

42:09.000 --> 42:12.000
Did I find a nice hotel?

42:12.000 --> 42:15.000
Did I find a nice hotel?

42:15.000 --> 42:17.000
Yes, I do.

42:17.000 --> 42:20.000
Well, was the hotel nice?

42:20.000 --> 42:21.000
Oh, yes.

42:21.000 --> 42:22.000
Very nice.

42:22.000 --> 42:26.000
Single room, very warm and breakfast in bed.

42:26.000 --> 42:27.000
Wonderful.

42:27.000 --> 42:29.000
And I didn't have to pay.

42:29.000 --> 42:31.000
What do you mean you don't have to pay?

42:31.000 --> 42:33.000
I didn't have to pay.

42:33.000 --> 42:36.000
I stayed in a police station cell last night.

42:36.000 --> 42:37.000
What?

42:37.000 --> 42:39.000
You're joking, aren't you?

42:39.000 --> 42:40.000
No.

42:40.000 --> 42:42.000
I am not joking.

42:42.000 --> 42:45.000
Last night I was taken to the police station.

42:45.000 --> 42:48.000
After you threw me out of the hotel last night,

42:48.000 --> 42:51.000
I tried to sleep in the car as it was so late.

42:51.000 --> 42:54.000
But Boris was barking and barking.

42:54.000 --> 42:56.000
Someone phoned the police,

42:56.000 --> 43:00.000
and then this unfriendly policeman knocked on my car window and...

43:00.000 --> 43:02.000
How old was he?

43:02.000 --> 43:03.000
What?

43:03.000 --> 43:05.000
Why do you want to know how old he was?

43:05.000 --> 43:07.000
I like young policemen.

43:07.000 --> 43:10.000
It gives me goose pimples all over.

43:10.000 --> 43:12.000
Do you know he's there?

43:12.000 --> 43:13.000
No, I don't.

43:13.000 --> 43:15.000
Where is Boris?

43:15.000 --> 43:17.000
What? Boris?

43:17.000 --> 43:18.000
He's in the car.

43:18.000 --> 43:20.000
I don't want to see him today.

43:20.000 --> 43:22.000
In the car?

43:22.000 --> 43:24.000
Oh, no.

43:24.000 --> 43:26.000
Did you see Rob...

43:26.000 --> 43:28.000
Mum's mobile.

43:28.000 --> 43:29.000
Mum's mobile?

43:29.000 --> 43:31.000
What are you talking about?

43:31.000 --> 43:35.000
I was in a police station last night and all you can ask about is Mum's mobile.

43:35.000 --> 43:37.000
I can't find it.

43:37.000 --> 43:39.000
Don't you understand?

43:39.000 --> 43:41.000
I am now a criminal.

43:41.000 --> 43:44.000
It's not so terrible, Pete.

43:44.000 --> 43:45.000
Yes, it is.

43:45.000 --> 43:47.000
I got a parking ticket last year.

43:47.000 --> 43:49.000
I left the car five minutes.

43:49.000 --> 43:51.000
A parking ticket?

43:51.000 --> 43:53.000
A parking ticket?

43:53.000 --> 43:56.000
I slept in a police cell last night, Nancy.

43:56.000 --> 43:58.000
Don't you understand?

43:58.000 --> 44:00.000
I can't go anywhere now.

44:00.000 --> 44:03.000
Every policeman now has a photo of me.

44:03.000 --> 44:05.000
I can't leave the hotel.

44:05.000 --> 44:06.000
It took me so stupid.

44:06.000 --> 44:09.000
You're here now, so come on and get ready.

44:09.000 --> 44:12.000
We want to start enjoying the holiday.

44:12.000 --> 44:14.000
Aren't you interested to know what happened?

44:14.000 --> 44:16.000
Must you go to prison?

44:16.000 --> 44:17.000
How many years?

44:17.000 --> 44:19.000
Maybe you can never come home again.

44:19.000 --> 44:22.000
I can make a cake for you with a file in it.

44:22.000 --> 44:24.000
No, Mum.

44:24.000 --> 44:26.000
Pete doesn't have to go to prison.

44:26.000 --> 44:28.000
He can stay with us.

44:28.000 --> 44:30.000
That's good news, isn't it?

44:30.000 --> 44:31.000
Um...

44:31.000 --> 44:35.000
I want to go to the beach in my new red bikini.

44:35.000 --> 44:37.000
Are you coming with me, Josephine?

44:37.000 --> 44:38.000
Nancy?

44:38.000 --> 44:39.000
Yes, I'm coming.

44:39.000 --> 44:42.000
I just want to look in the car for Rob...

44:42.000 --> 44:43.000
Er...

44:43.000 --> 44:44.000
You're mobile, Mum.

44:44.000 --> 44:46.000
Thank you, Josie.

44:46.000 --> 44:48.000
I'm coming too, Mum.

44:48.000 --> 44:51.000
First I want to speak to Luigi.

44:51.000 --> 44:56.000
This morning at breakfast, he said he now has two rooms for us for the rest of the week.

44:56.000 --> 44:59.000
I just want to say thank you.

44:59.000 --> 45:01.000
Just wait for me then. Give me two...

45:03.000 --> 45:06.000
Minutes to get ready.

45:17.000 --> 45:21.000
It's nice to see the sun and smell the fresh air.

45:21.000 --> 45:23.000
In prison, it was...

45:23.000 --> 45:24.000
We know, Pete.

45:24.000 --> 45:27.000
You told us the same story ten minutes ago.

45:27.000 --> 45:29.000
Don't you want to hear what happened to me?

45:29.000 --> 45:33.000
We're now lying on the beach and relaxing.

45:33.000 --> 45:36.000
Can we forget prisons and policemen?

45:36.000 --> 45:40.000
I can tell all my friends at school that my father is a criminal.

45:40.000 --> 45:42.000
No, you can't, Josephine.

45:42.000 --> 45:46.000
Did you see the prisoners on death row and the electric chair?

45:46.000 --> 45:48.000
You watch too many films.

45:48.000 --> 45:51.000
What is your mother wearing, Nancy?

45:51.000 --> 45:52.000
I can't believe it.

45:52.000 --> 45:55.000
Everyone on the beach is looking and laughing.

45:55.000 --> 45:56.000
Say something to her.

45:56.000 --> 46:00.000
I told her not to wear it, but she didn't listen.

46:00.000 --> 46:01.000
She looks like...

46:01.000 --> 46:03.000
She looks like...

46:03.000 --> 46:05.000
It's the bikini she's wearing.

46:05.000 --> 46:09.000
A bottom looks like two half-deflated hot air balloons.

46:09.000 --> 46:10.000
No, I can't look.

46:10.000 --> 46:11.000
Makes me feel ill.

46:11.000 --> 46:12.000
Look at the other way.

46:12.000 --> 46:14.000
It's difficult to look the other way.

46:14.000 --> 46:16.000
I know what you mean.

46:16.000 --> 46:19.000
Oh, there are some really thick guys on the beach.

46:19.000 --> 46:21.000
Really awesome.

46:21.000 --> 46:23.000
You all right, Josie?

46:23.000 --> 46:24.000
See you soon.

46:24.000 --> 46:25.000
Where are you going, mother?

46:25.000 --> 46:26.000
Excellent.

46:26.000 --> 46:27.000
Don't worry.

46:27.000 --> 46:30.000
What is your mother doing now?

46:30.000 --> 46:31.000
Why is she talking to him?

46:31.000 --> 46:33.000
Oh, he's real fit.

46:33.000 --> 46:34.000
Stop it, Josie.

46:34.000 --> 46:36.000
I don't know what she's doing.

46:36.000 --> 46:38.000
I really don't know.

46:38.000 --> 46:39.000
No.

46:43.000 --> 46:46.000
Excuse me, young man.

46:46.000 --> 46:49.000
It would be really nice if you could help me.

46:49.000 --> 46:51.000
What's the matter, dear?

46:51.000 --> 46:54.000
I'm not as young as I used to be, and I...

46:54.000 --> 46:55.000
No problem.

46:55.000 --> 46:57.000
What can I do for you?

46:57.000 --> 46:58.000
Put up your deck chair?

46:58.000 --> 46:59.000
No.

46:59.000 --> 47:00.000
Carry your bag?

47:00.000 --> 47:01.000
No.

47:01.000 --> 47:03.000
Just tell me what you want.

47:03.000 --> 47:04.000
Happy to help you?

47:04.000 --> 47:07.000
Can you rub some suntan oil over my body?

47:08.000 --> 47:09.000
What?

47:09.000 --> 47:15.000
Well, I'm very busy at the moment.

47:15.000 --> 47:18.000
I'm allergic to suntan oil.

47:18.000 --> 47:21.000
I think my wife is waving at me.

47:21.000 --> 47:22.000
Must go.

47:22.000 --> 47:23.000
Bye.

47:23.000 --> 47:25.000
Maybe tomorrow.

47:25.000 --> 47:27.000
I'm leaving today.

47:27.000 --> 47:28.000
What a pity.

47:33.000 --> 47:35.000
What did you do, mother?

47:35.000 --> 47:36.000
Why is he running away?

47:36.000 --> 47:38.000
I just asked him to help me.

47:38.000 --> 47:40.000
What did you ask him to do?

47:40.000 --> 47:42.000
Nothing much.

47:42.000 --> 47:48.000
Nancy, do you think I can take my bikini off to get an oil over body turn?

47:48.000 --> 47:50.000
No, you cannot!

47:50.000 --> 47:53.000
I want an ice cream, Mum.

47:53.000 --> 47:55.000
I want some money.

47:55.000 --> 47:56.000
Here you are.

47:56.000 --> 47:59.000
Can you get us all an ice cream, Josie?

47:59.000 --> 48:00.000
You can choose.

48:00.000 --> 48:02.000
Okay.

48:02.000 --> 48:05.000
I can go and see if Boris is okay and look for...

48:06.000 --> 48:08.000
Er... something.

48:08.000 --> 48:13.000
Your daughter is saying some very strange things these days, Nancy.

48:13.000 --> 48:15.000
She's your daughter as well.

48:15.000 --> 48:16.000
Oh, yes.

48:16.000 --> 48:18.000
I suppose she is.

48:22.000 --> 48:23.000
Here you are.

48:23.000 --> 48:25.000
Ice cream is for everyone.

48:25.000 --> 48:26.000
Thank you.

48:26.000 --> 48:29.000
Boris is unhappy in the car alone.

48:29.000 --> 48:32.000
The ice cream man was really buff.

48:32.000 --> 48:34.000
Great body.

48:35.000 --> 48:36.000
What does that mean?

48:36.000 --> 48:38.000
Oh, you're so old.

48:38.000 --> 48:39.000
Don't you know?

48:39.000 --> 48:41.000
When I was young...

48:41.000 --> 48:43.000
Oh, yes, Dad. Not again.

48:43.000 --> 48:45.000
It gave me his phone number.

48:45.000 --> 48:46.000
You are not meeting him.

48:46.000 --> 48:47.000
You are too young.

48:47.000 --> 48:49.000
Why not?

48:49.000 --> 48:51.000
That's not fair.

48:51.000 --> 48:53.000
He asked me for a drink.

48:53.000 --> 48:54.000
That's all.

48:54.000 --> 48:55.000
We can all come with you.

48:55.000 --> 48:56.000
What?

48:56.000 --> 48:58.000
Let her go by herself.

48:58.000 --> 48:59.000
Don't interfere.

48:59.000 --> 49:00.000
She's our daughter.

49:00.000 --> 49:03.000
I think it's okay for Josie to meet him.

49:03.000 --> 49:05.000
It's only for a drink.

49:05.000 --> 49:07.000
Don't you trust your daughter, Pete?

49:07.000 --> 49:09.000
She is too young.

49:09.000 --> 49:11.000
You know that he wants more than a drink.

49:11.000 --> 49:15.000
Is it the man on the promenade with long black hair, Josie?

49:15.000 --> 49:16.000
Yes.

49:16.000 --> 49:19.000
He smiled at me, too, when I walked past.

49:19.000 --> 49:22.000
I used to be attractive to men, Josie.

49:22.000 --> 49:24.000
Which century was that?

49:24.000 --> 49:26.000
The Middle Ages, before they invented the wheel.

49:26.000 --> 49:28.000
I ought to meet him.

49:28.000 --> 49:30.000
I don't care what you say.

49:30.000 --> 49:31.000
You do as I tell you.

49:31.000 --> 49:33.000
Nancy, speak to your daughter.

49:33.000 --> 49:34.000
Why ask me?

49:34.000 --> 49:36.000
You can speak to her yourself.

49:36.000 --> 49:38.000
I can go with Josie to meet him.

49:38.000 --> 49:40.000
Is that all right?

49:40.000 --> 49:41.000
Pete?

49:41.000 --> 49:44.000
I suppose so.

49:44.000 --> 49:46.000
But you know what your mother is like.

49:46.000 --> 49:48.000
She's very sensible.

49:48.000 --> 49:49.000
Hmm.

49:49.000 --> 49:50.000
I'm not so sure.

49:50.000 --> 49:51.000
Oh, no.

49:51.000 --> 49:52.000
Look.

49:52.000 --> 49:54.000
It's getting cloudy.

49:54.000 --> 49:56.000
Where's the sun gone?

49:56.000 --> 49:58.000
She think it's going to rain.

49:58.000 --> 50:01.000
Typical bloody, nothing black or weather.

50:01.000 --> 50:03.000
It's getting cold.

50:03.000 --> 50:05.000
Let's go back to the hotel.

50:05.000 --> 50:07.000
Mother, you can change out of that bikini.

50:07.000 --> 50:10.000
And then we can go to the pleasure beach this afternoon.

50:10.000 --> 50:13.000
Can we go on the ghost train together?

50:13.000 --> 50:15.000
I want to sit at the front.

50:15.000 --> 50:17.000
And I want some candy floss.

50:17.000 --> 50:20.000
She gets more like a child each day.

50:20.000 --> 50:23.000
I really think we must go and see her doctor when we get home.

50:23.000 --> 50:25.000
Pete, please don't say that.

50:25.000 --> 50:28.000
Can we just try to have a nice day?

50:28.000 --> 50:29.000
Yes, dear.

50:29.000 --> 50:31.000
Come on, everyone.

50:31.000 --> 50:33.000
Bring all our things.

50:33.000 --> 50:34.000
Ooh.

50:34.000 --> 50:35.000
Hurry up, Josie.

50:35.000 --> 50:37.000
Mom, bring the towels and the sunshade.

50:37.000 --> 50:39.000
Don't forget your sunglasses.

50:39.000 --> 50:40.000
Yes, Mom.

50:40.000 --> 50:41.000
Yes, Mom.

50:41.000 --> 50:43.000
Don't go on all the time.

50:43.000 --> 50:44.000
Thanks, Grand.

50:44.000 --> 50:47.000
We can sort something out when we're alone.

50:48.000 --> 50:50.000
Ooh, it's stuck to my nose.

50:50.000 --> 50:51.000
Help me, Nancy.

50:51.000 --> 50:52.000
Help me.

50:52.000 --> 50:53.000
It's OK, Grand.

50:53.000 --> 50:54.000
Let me help you.

50:54.000 --> 50:56.000
But candy floss is such fun.

50:56.000 --> 50:57.000
I like it.

50:57.000 --> 51:00.000
It is so sweet and sticky.

51:00.000 --> 51:02.000
Oh, Pete.

51:02.000 --> 51:06.000
It's so good to see Mother enjoying herself.

51:06.000 --> 51:08.000
I hope Josephine looks so good.

51:08.000 --> 51:09.000
It's so sweet.

51:09.000 --> 51:10.000
It's so sweet.

51:10.000 --> 51:11.000
Oh, Pete.

51:11.000 --> 51:14.000
It's so good to see Mother enjoying herself.

51:15.000 --> 51:18.000
I hope Josephine looks after us when we're old.

51:18.000 --> 51:20.000
I'm not so sure, Nancy.

51:20.000 --> 51:22.000
It's a different generation.

51:22.000 --> 51:24.000
What do we do when we're old?

51:24.000 --> 51:26.000
I don't know.

51:26.000 --> 51:27.000
I don't know.

51:27.000 --> 51:28.000
Come on, everyone.

51:28.000 --> 51:30.000
To the ghost train.

51:30.000 --> 51:32.000
I'm coming with you, Grand.

51:32.000 --> 51:34.000
Mom and Dad are so naff.

51:34.000 --> 51:35.000
You do go.

51:35.000 --> 51:39.000
We want to sit in a cafe and have a quiet cup of tea.

51:39.000 --> 51:41.000
We can make here in a couple of hours.

51:41.000 --> 51:43.000
You're on holiday.

51:43.000 --> 51:44.000
Relax.

51:44.000 --> 51:45.000
I'm fun.

51:45.000 --> 51:49.000
Going on a ghost train is not my idea of fun.

51:49.000 --> 51:50.000
You go.

51:50.000 --> 51:51.000
Okay.

51:51.000 --> 51:52.000
Grand?

51:52.000 --> 51:53.000
Yes, Josie.

51:53.000 --> 51:56.000
Can I ask you a big favor?

51:56.000 --> 51:59.000
Of course, my dear.

51:59.000 --> 52:02.000
Please, don't tell Mom and Dad.

52:02.000 --> 52:06.000
I want to go and see that barfly screen man.

52:06.000 --> 52:08.000
Is it okay?

52:08.000 --> 52:10.000
Of course, Josie.

52:10.000 --> 52:11.000
Have fun.

52:11.000 --> 52:14.000
You're only young once in your life.

52:14.000 --> 52:16.000
I'm happy by myself.

52:16.000 --> 52:22.000
Maybe there will be a lovely rich widower sitting next to me on the ghost train.

52:22.000 --> 52:24.000
Bye, Grand.

52:24.000 --> 52:25.000
Bye.

52:30.000 --> 52:32.000
Well, what a holiday.

52:32.000 --> 52:36.000
I hope the rest of the week is more peaceful and with no more disasters.

52:36.000 --> 52:39.000
Don't forget, we have to go home in your car.

52:39.000 --> 52:41.000
That is a disaster.

52:41.000 --> 52:42.000
Okay.

52:42.000 --> 52:43.000
Okay.

52:43.000 --> 52:44.000
Not again.

52:44.000 --> 52:45.000
Can we change the subject?

52:45.000 --> 52:46.000
You started it.

52:46.000 --> 52:48.000
You mentioned disasters, not me.

52:48.000 --> 52:50.000
You mentioned the car, not me.

52:50.000 --> 52:52.000
Not so loud.

52:52.000 --> 52:55.000
Everyone is listening to us.

52:55.000 --> 52:58.000
What's that in your teacup?

52:58.000 --> 53:00.000
It's moving.

53:00.000 --> 53:01.000
What?

53:01.000 --> 53:02.000
Where?

53:02.000 --> 53:03.000
Oh, no.

53:03.000 --> 53:04.000
It's a fly.

53:04.000 --> 53:05.000
I don't believe it.

53:05.000 --> 53:08.000
There's a fly swimming in my Earl Grey.

53:08.000 --> 53:09.000
Do something then.

53:09.000 --> 53:11.000
Don't just look at it.

53:11.000 --> 53:12.000
Give me the newspaper.

53:12.000 --> 53:14.000
No, don't do that.

53:14.000 --> 53:17.000
Oh, why did you do that?

53:17.000 --> 53:19.000
You're so stupid.

53:19.000 --> 53:20.000
I killed the fly.

53:20.000 --> 53:22.000
Oh, yes, you killed the fly.

53:22.000 --> 53:25.000
But your hot tea went all over my dress.

53:25.000 --> 53:27.000
Look what happened.

53:27.000 --> 53:28.000
It's not so bad.

53:28.000 --> 53:29.000
Yes, it is.

53:29.000 --> 53:31.000
Look, I can't wear this.

53:31.000 --> 53:32.000
You can wash it.

53:32.000 --> 53:33.000
No problem.

53:33.000 --> 53:34.000
Why can't you wash it?

53:35.000 --> 53:40.000
Why is life so difficult with you, Pete?

53:40.000 --> 53:43.000
I don't know what you mean.

53:43.000 --> 53:48.000
We came to Blackpool to have a holiday, but so far it isn't happening.

53:48.000 --> 53:52.000
I'm going back to the hotel to have a rest on the bed.

53:52.000 --> 53:55.000
Bit of peace and quiet is what I need now.

53:55.000 --> 53:57.000
I can come with you.

53:57.000 --> 53:58.000
No, no.

53:58.000 --> 53:59.000
It's okay.

53:59.000 --> 54:02.000
You stay here and destroy some more cups.

54:02.000 --> 54:06.000
You can meet Mum and Josie and then come back to the hotel later.

54:06.000 --> 54:08.000
If you think that is the best thing to do.

54:08.000 --> 54:10.000
Yes, yes, definitely.

54:10.000 --> 54:12.000
Okay, Nancy.

54:12.000 --> 54:15.000
Go to bed if you think it's what you need.

54:15.000 --> 54:18.000
I think bed is a good idea.

54:18.000 --> 54:21.000
A very good idea.

54:21.000 --> 54:23.000
See you later.

54:26.000 --> 54:28.000
Can I pay, please?

54:28.000 --> 54:31.000
Yes, sorry about the cups.

54:31.000 --> 54:34.000
My wife got angry and had an accident.

54:34.000 --> 54:35.000
Women.

54:42.000 --> 54:44.000
Oh, hello, Grand.

54:44.000 --> 54:46.000
Josephine, not with you?

54:46.000 --> 54:47.000
Hello.

54:47.000 --> 54:51.000
No, Josephine is licking an ice cream.

54:51.000 --> 54:52.000
What is the matter?

54:52.000 --> 54:53.000
My tooth.

54:53.000 --> 54:55.000
I lost them.

54:55.000 --> 54:57.000
How did you do that?

54:57.000 --> 54:59.000
I went on the Dodgeham cars.

54:59.000 --> 55:03.000
And this nice widow had knocked into me and they went flying into the air.

55:03.000 --> 55:04.000
Oh, dear.

55:04.000 --> 55:06.000
Oh, dear.

55:06.000 --> 55:08.000
What a pity.

55:08.000 --> 55:09.000
Hope you find them.

55:09.000 --> 55:11.000
You can't eat without them.

55:11.000 --> 55:13.000
I spare pear as at home.

55:13.000 --> 55:14.000
Pity.

55:14.000 --> 55:16.000
Maybe you can get a straw in the hotel.

55:16.000 --> 55:18.000
That's a good idea.

55:18.000 --> 55:20.000
Well, have fun.

55:20.000 --> 55:22.000
I'm walking around the pleasure beach for a while.

55:22.000 --> 55:24.000
Nancy is back at the hotel.

55:24.000 --> 55:25.000
Bye.

55:25.000 --> 55:26.000
Bye.

55:28.000 --> 55:33.000
Where's my car?

55:33.000 --> 55:35.000
It's not in the car park.

55:35.000 --> 55:36.000
It's stolen.

55:36.000 --> 55:37.000
Can someone help?

55:37.000 --> 55:38.000
Where is everyone?

55:38.000 --> 55:40.000
Where's that Italian manager?

55:40.000 --> 55:43.000
When you want someone, call the police.

55:43.000 --> 55:45.000
Nancy?

55:45.000 --> 55:48.000
Nancy, open the door.

55:48.000 --> 55:49.000
Throw in the police.

55:49.000 --> 55:51.000
My car, it's stolen.

55:51.000 --> 55:53.000
Open the door.

55:53.000 --> 55:55.000
Where is everyone?

55:55.000 --> 55:57.000
Are you asleep?

55:57.000 --> 55:59.000
I don't believe it.

55:59.000 --> 56:00.000
Where is she?

56:00.000 --> 56:01.000
Women.

56:01.000 --> 56:03.000
Of course.

56:03.000 --> 56:04.000
My mobile.

56:04.000 --> 56:06.000
I have it in my pocket.

56:06.000 --> 56:07.000
Nine.

56:07.000 --> 56:08.000
Nine.

56:08.000 --> 56:09.000
Nine.

56:09.000 --> 56:12.000
Hello?

56:12.000 --> 56:14.000
Yes, it's an emergency.

56:14.000 --> 56:15.000
Police.

56:15.000 --> 56:17.000
My car is stolen.

56:17.000 --> 56:19.000
Hotel Grand Park.

56:19.000 --> 56:21.000
On the seafront.

56:22.000 --> 56:27.000
Registration F-H-W-2-9-6-K.

56:27.000 --> 56:29.000
What?

56:29.000 --> 56:30.000
My name?

56:30.000 --> 56:32.000
I'm Britain.

56:32.000 --> 56:33.000
Pete Britain.

56:33.000 --> 56:35.000
Come quickly.

56:38.000 --> 56:39.000
What's the problem, Dad?

56:39.000 --> 56:41.000
I can hear you from outside.

56:41.000 --> 56:42.000
The car.

56:42.000 --> 56:43.000
It's stolen.

56:43.000 --> 56:44.000
God!

56:44.000 --> 56:45.000
Where's Boris?

56:45.000 --> 56:46.000
What?

56:46.000 --> 56:47.000
Who?

56:47.000 --> 56:48.000
Oh, Boris.

56:48.000 --> 56:49.000
I don't know.

56:49.000 --> 56:50.000
In the car.

56:51.000 --> 56:52.000
Driving the car.

56:52.000 --> 56:53.000
Come down, Dad.

56:53.000 --> 56:54.000
Don't get hysterical.

56:54.000 --> 56:56.000
Boris can't drive the car.

56:56.000 --> 56:57.000
He's too young.

56:57.000 --> 56:59.000
He doesn't have a license.

56:59.000 --> 57:01.000
What are you talking about?

57:01.000 --> 57:02.000
Boris doesn't have a license.

57:02.000 --> 57:04.000
What are you talking about?

57:04.000 --> 57:05.000
It's a joke, Dad.

57:05.000 --> 57:06.000
Stay cool.

57:06.000 --> 57:08.000
I am cool.

57:10.000 --> 57:11.000
The police are here.

57:11.000 --> 57:12.000
Come on.

57:21.000 --> 57:23.000
Good morning, sir.

57:23.000 --> 57:25.000
Oh, no.

57:25.000 --> 57:26.000
It's you.

57:26.000 --> 57:28.000
Yes, it's me, sir.

57:28.000 --> 57:30.000
Nice to see you again, sir.

57:30.000 --> 57:31.000
Hmm.

57:31.000 --> 57:33.000
What's the problem, sir?

57:33.000 --> 57:34.000
My car.

57:34.000 --> 57:35.000
It's not in the car park.

57:35.000 --> 57:36.000
It's a classic car.

57:36.000 --> 57:38.000
It's probably sold by now.

57:38.000 --> 57:39.000
And it's out of the country.

57:39.000 --> 57:41.000
I don't think so, sir.

57:41.000 --> 57:43.000
How do you know?

57:43.000 --> 57:44.000
It's a very special car.

57:44.000 --> 57:46.000
There aren't many left in the world.

57:46.000 --> 57:48.000
Don't worry, sir.

57:48.000 --> 57:50.000
Of course I worry.

57:50.000 --> 57:51.000
It's my car.

57:51.000 --> 57:55.000
We found your car, sir, 20 minutes ago.

57:55.000 --> 57:56.000
Yes?

57:56.000 --> 57:57.000
Wonderful.

57:57.000 --> 57:58.000
Where is it?

57:58.000 --> 58:00.000
Where we found it, sir.

58:00.000 --> 58:01.000
Yes, sir.

58:01.000 --> 58:03.000
One mile from here.

58:03.000 --> 58:06.000
It broke down in the middle of the high streets.

58:06.000 --> 58:10.000
There is a three-mile traffic jam behind it, sir.

58:10.000 --> 58:17.000
No one can get into the car to move it because your mad dog attacks anyone who tries to get into it.

58:17.000 --> 58:19.000
My car is okay.

58:19.000 --> 58:25.000
We would be very grateful if you could come and move your car, sir, before we shoot your mad beast.

58:25.000 --> 58:27.000
You can't shoot, Boris.

58:27.000 --> 58:28.000
We can.

58:28.000 --> 58:30.000
We certainly can.

58:30.000 --> 58:35.000
So both of you come with me in my car now, please.

58:48.000 --> 58:50.000
Where is everyone?

58:50.000 --> 58:52.000
It's late.

58:52.000 --> 58:54.000
Don't worry, Nancy.

58:54.000 --> 58:56.000
Oh, here comes your mother.

58:56.000 --> 58:57.000
Oh, Nancy.

58:57.000 --> 58:59.000
I can't find them.

58:59.000 --> 59:01.000
I lost my teeth.

59:01.000 --> 59:02.000
What are you talking about?

59:02.000 --> 59:04.000
Oh, didn't Pete tell you?

59:04.000 --> 59:06.000
No, I was busy.

59:06.000 --> 59:08.000
Oh, anyway.

59:08.000 --> 59:09.000
What happened?

59:09.000 --> 59:10.000
Where's Josephine?

59:10.000 --> 59:12.000
She went off to have a bitter ice cream.

59:12.000 --> 59:14.000
Where is she now?

59:14.000 --> 59:16.000
And where is Pete?

59:16.000 --> 59:18.000
What a holiday.

59:18.000 --> 59:21.000
This nice widower helped me look.

59:21.000 --> 59:22.000
Who?

59:22.000 --> 59:23.000
Where?

59:23.000 --> 59:25.000
For your lost teeth?

59:25.000 --> 59:26.000
Yes.

59:26.000 --> 59:30.000
I crashed on the Dodgeham cars and they came out of my mouth.

59:30.000 --> 59:33.000
Oh, terrible mother.

59:33.000 --> 59:34.000
There you are.

59:34.000 --> 59:37.000
Oh, there you both are.

59:37.000 --> 59:38.000
What happened?

59:38.000 --> 59:40.000
I can ask you the same question.

59:40.000 --> 59:42.000
Where were you when I knocked on the bedroom door?

59:42.000 --> 59:45.000
The car was stolen with Boris inside.

59:45.000 --> 59:47.000
So now you must buy a new car.

59:47.000 --> 59:49.000
No, it's OK.

59:49.000 --> 59:51.000
The police found it in the High Street.

59:51.000 --> 59:52.000
What a pity.

59:52.000 --> 59:54.000
And where were you this afternoon, Josephine?

59:54.000 --> 59:57.000
I thought you were going on the ghost train with your grandmother.

59:57.000 --> 01:00:00.000
You weren't with your grandmother, Josephine?

01:00:00.000 --> 01:00:02.000
No, I, er...

01:00:02.000 --> 01:00:04.000
went shopping for clothes.

01:00:04.000 --> 01:00:07.000
Your grandmother told me you went for an ice cream.

01:00:07.000 --> 01:00:09.000
Er, that as well.

01:00:09.000 --> 01:00:11.000
I am confused.

01:00:11.000 --> 01:00:13.000
I don't know where I am.

01:00:13.000 --> 01:00:16.000
Is this all so important?

01:00:16.000 --> 01:00:19.000
I think we all need a nice cup of tea.

01:00:19.000 --> 01:00:21.000
You're right, Mum.

01:00:21.000 --> 01:00:26.000
Luigi, can we all have some tea and cakes in the restaurant, please?

01:00:26.000 --> 01:00:29.000
Yes, of course.

01:00:29.000 --> 01:00:34.000
And can you book us a table in your restaurant for a celebration tomorrow evening?

01:00:34.000 --> 01:00:36.000
Of course, Nancy.

01:00:36.000 --> 01:00:38.000
What is the occasion?

01:00:38.000 --> 01:00:41.000
It's my birthday, but I don't feel like celebrating.

01:00:41.000 --> 01:00:44.000
Perhaps something revealing is going to happen.

01:00:44.000 --> 01:00:47.000
The naked truth?

01:00:47.000 --> 01:00:49.000
Are you talking about?

01:00:49.000 --> 01:00:52.000
I don't understand, women.

01:00:52.000 --> 01:00:55.000
Wait and see!

01:00:55.000 --> 01:00:57.000
Wait, Nancy!

01:00:58.000 --> 01:01:00.000
This is nice, isn't it?

01:01:00.000 --> 01:01:02.000
I don't like the food.

01:01:02.000 --> 01:01:04.000
It's foreign muck.

01:01:04.000 --> 01:01:07.000
I don't understand the menus.

01:01:07.000 --> 01:01:09.000
Stop moaning.

01:01:09.000 --> 01:01:11.000
This is my birthday.

01:01:11.000 --> 01:01:14.000
Oh, you're having a nice time, aren't we?

01:01:14.000 --> 01:01:17.000
I can't eat this maple tea.

01:01:17.000 --> 01:01:19.000
I don't like the food.

01:01:19.000 --> 01:01:21.000
It's foreign muck.

01:01:21.000 --> 01:01:23.000
I don't understand the menus.

01:01:23.000 --> 01:01:24.000
Stop moaning.

01:01:24.000 --> 01:01:26.000
This is my birthday.

01:01:26.000 --> 01:01:30.000
This meat without my teeth and this straw doesn't help.

01:01:30.000 --> 01:01:32.000
Mother, please.

01:01:32.000 --> 01:01:34.000
Don't make that noise.

01:01:34.000 --> 01:01:37.000
It's difficult to eat, Nancy.

01:01:37.000 --> 01:01:40.000
Can I ask the waiter to cut up my meat?

01:01:40.000 --> 01:01:42.000
No, you can't.

01:01:42.000 --> 01:01:44.000
Let me do it.

01:01:44.000 --> 01:01:48.000
Do you like your meal, Pete?

01:01:48.000 --> 01:01:51.000
It's okay, but it's very expensive.

01:01:51.000 --> 01:01:54.000
I prefer fish and chips.

01:01:54.000 --> 01:01:57.000
I thought this would be nice for your birthday.

01:01:57.000 --> 01:01:59.000
Yes, dear.

01:01:59.000 --> 01:02:00.000
Thank you, dear.

01:02:00.000 --> 01:02:02.000
Oh, look over there!

01:02:02.000 --> 01:02:03.000
Where, Mum?

01:02:03.000 --> 01:02:04.000
There!

01:02:04.000 --> 01:02:06.000
It's the lovely widower who helped me yesterday.

01:02:06.000 --> 01:02:08.000
Which one, Grand?

01:02:08.000 --> 01:02:09.000
Him!

01:02:09.000 --> 01:02:10.000
Opposite her!

01:02:10.000 --> 01:02:12.000
Next to the other man with the shirt.

01:02:12.000 --> 01:02:13.000
Try!

01:02:13.000 --> 01:02:14.000
Ooh!

01:02:14.000 --> 01:02:15.000
Hurry!

01:02:15.000 --> 01:02:17.000
Mum, stop it.

01:02:17.000 --> 01:02:18.000
Stop waving.

01:02:18.000 --> 01:02:20.000
Your mother is impossible.

01:02:20.000 --> 01:02:22.000
Do something, Nancy.

01:02:22.000 --> 01:02:23.000
What do you suggest?

01:02:23.000 --> 01:02:27.000
Tying her to the chair and potting her sock in her mouth is a good idea.

01:02:27.000 --> 01:02:29.000
He's coming to our table.

01:02:29.000 --> 01:02:31.000
Oh, lovely.

01:02:31.000 --> 01:02:33.000
Oh, he has my teeth.

01:02:33.000 --> 01:02:35.000
He found my teeth.

01:02:35.000 --> 01:02:37.000
Oh, thank you so much.

01:02:37.000 --> 01:02:40.000
Let me give you a big kiss.

01:02:40.000 --> 01:02:42.000
Oh, come on, Mum.

01:02:42.000 --> 01:02:43.000
Sit down.

01:02:43.000 --> 01:02:45.000
Everyone in the restaurant is watching.

01:02:45.000 --> 01:02:47.000
But I'm so happy.

01:02:47.000 --> 01:02:49.000
I have my teeth.

01:02:50.000 --> 01:02:52.000
Ah!

01:02:52.000 --> 01:02:55.000
Now I can eat this meat.

01:02:55.000 --> 01:02:57.000
Oh, that's much better.

01:02:57.000 --> 01:02:59.000
I suddenly don't feel like eating anymore.

01:02:59.000 --> 01:03:01.000
Sorry, Nancy.

01:03:01.000 --> 01:03:03.000
I understand.

01:03:03.000 --> 01:03:05.000
Why have you stopped eating, Pete?

01:03:05.000 --> 01:03:07.000
I feel so hungry now.

01:03:07.000 --> 01:03:09.000
Did me your plate.

01:03:09.000 --> 01:03:11.000
I can eat your dinner as well.

01:03:11.000 --> 01:03:13.000
I don't believe it.

01:03:13.000 --> 01:03:16.000
Oh, no.

01:03:16.000 --> 01:03:19.000
Look, they're the police.

01:03:19.000 --> 01:03:21.000
I know they're looking for me.

01:03:21.000 --> 01:03:22.000
Help me, Nancy.

01:03:22.000 --> 01:03:23.000
Don't let us see me.

01:03:23.000 --> 01:03:25.000
Oh, don't be so stupid.

01:03:25.000 --> 01:03:30.000
She's not looking for you.

01:03:30.000 --> 01:03:32.000
Well, she's coming to our table.

01:03:32.000 --> 01:03:35.000
I think she is looking for you.

01:03:35.000 --> 01:03:36.000
Pete?

01:03:36.000 --> 01:03:38.000
Pete, where are you?

01:03:38.000 --> 01:03:40.000
I'm under the table.

01:03:40.000 --> 01:03:42.000
Don't tell her I'm here.

01:03:42.000 --> 01:03:44.000
Say I'm not here.

01:03:44.000 --> 01:03:46.000
Say I went to Spain.

01:03:46.000 --> 01:03:50.000
Or I'm at the dentist or anything.

01:03:50.000 --> 01:03:51.000
Stupid Pete.

01:03:51.000 --> 01:03:52.000
Sit in your chair.

01:03:52.000 --> 01:03:54.000
She's going to arrest you, Pete.

01:03:54.000 --> 01:03:56.000
Oh, how exciting.

01:03:56.000 --> 01:03:58.000
Over here, Constable.

01:03:58.000 --> 01:04:00.000
He's hiding under the table.

01:04:00.000 --> 01:04:02.000
Here it is.

01:04:02.000 --> 01:04:04.000
Thank you very, very much.

01:04:04.000 --> 01:04:05.000
Just you wait.

01:04:05.000 --> 01:04:07.000
You wait.

01:04:07.000 --> 01:04:08.000
Oh!

01:04:08.000 --> 01:04:10.000
Hello, Constable.

01:04:10.000 --> 01:04:13.000
I was just picking up my shoelace.

01:04:13.000 --> 01:04:15.000
I'm trying up my serviette.

01:04:15.000 --> 01:04:16.000
No.

01:04:16.000 --> 01:04:18.000
What is happening?

01:04:18.000 --> 01:04:21.000
You don't look like a real police woman.

01:04:21.000 --> 01:04:22.000
Wait.

01:04:22.000 --> 01:04:23.000
You...

01:04:23.000 --> 01:04:24.000
Wearing...

01:04:24.000 --> 01:04:26.000
High heels.

01:04:26.000 --> 01:04:27.000
And...

01:04:27.000 --> 01:04:28.000
Lipstick.

01:04:28.000 --> 01:04:30.000
Short...

01:04:30.000 --> 01:04:31.000
Skirt.

01:04:31.000 --> 01:04:36.000
Excuse me, you sir.

01:04:36.000 --> 01:04:39.000
Why are you taking off your uniform?

01:04:39.000 --> 01:04:42.000
It's not hot in here.

01:04:42.000 --> 01:04:44.000
What are you doing?

01:04:44.000 --> 01:04:45.000
Please stop it.

01:04:45.000 --> 01:04:46.000
Now...

01:04:46.000 --> 01:04:48.000
It's okay, Nancy.

01:04:48.000 --> 01:04:49.000
It's fun.

01:04:49.000 --> 01:04:51.000
I feel like joining myself.

01:04:51.000 --> 01:04:53.000
Don't bother.

01:04:53.000 --> 01:04:54.000
Pete.

01:04:54.000 --> 01:04:55.000
Do something.

01:04:55.000 --> 01:04:57.000
Everyone is looking.

01:04:57.000 --> 01:04:59.000
Put your tongue back in your mouth.

01:04:59.000 --> 01:05:00.000
You look stupid.

01:05:00.000 --> 01:05:02.000
Oh.

01:05:02.000 --> 01:05:03.000
Hello.

01:05:03.000 --> 01:05:04.000
Oh, no.

01:05:04.000 --> 01:05:05.000
Ah, yes.

01:05:05.000 --> 01:05:07.000
Whose idea is this?

01:05:07.000 --> 01:05:08.000
Stop now, please.

01:05:08.000 --> 01:05:11.000
It's a stipper ground for Pete's birthday.

01:05:11.000 --> 01:05:13.000
I organized it with Josie.

01:05:13.000 --> 01:05:15.000
Happy birthday, Pete.

01:05:15.000 --> 01:05:18.000
I don't think it is a very good present.

01:05:18.000 --> 01:05:22.000
What do you think, Pete?

01:05:22.000 --> 01:05:23.000
Pete?

01:05:23.000 --> 01:05:24.000
Yes, dear.

01:05:24.000 --> 01:05:25.000
Whatever you say, dear.

01:05:25.000 --> 01:05:26.000
Stop this now.

01:05:26.000 --> 01:05:27.000
Oh, my God.

01:05:27.000 --> 01:05:28.000
They're not real.

01:05:28.000 --> 01:05:29.000
They can't be.

01:05:29.000 --> 01:05:30.000
No, dear.

01:05:30.000 --> 01:05:31.000
Yes, dear.

01:05:31.000 --> 01:05:32.000
Whatever you say to you.

01:05:32.000 --> 01:05:33.000
Green.

01:05:33.000 --> 01:05:34.000
Look.

01:05:34.000 --> 01:05:35.000
Watch the matter, Jos.

01:05:35.000 --> 01:05:36.000
Look.

01:05:36.000 --> 01:05:37.000
It's...

01:05:37.000 --> 01:05:38.000
No, it's Robbie.

01:05:38.000 --> 01:05:39.000
Where?

01:05:39.000 --> 01:05:40.000
Behind Dad.

01:05:40.000 --> 01:05:41.000
Oh.

01:05:41.000 --> 01:05:44.000
He's walking around the place on one's stripper's foot.

01:05:44.000 --> 01:05:46.000
Don't something grind?

01:05:46.000 --> 01:05:48.000
What's the matter with you two?

01:05:48.000 --> 01:05:49.000
Oh.

01:05:49.000 --> 01:05:50.000
Nothing, Mum.

01:05:50.000 --> 01:05:52.000
What a birthday.

01:05:52.000 --> 01:05:54.000
What a birthday.

01:05:58.000 --> 01:06:00.000
What happened?

01:06:00.000 --> 01:06:01.000
I was enjoying that.

01:06:01.000 --> 01:06:02.000
Where is she?

01:06:02.000 --> 01:06:03.000
Why is she screaming?

01:06:03.000 --> 01:06:04.000
I didn't touch her.

01:06:04.000 --> 01:06:05.000
Come on, Grant.

01:06:05.000 --> 01:06:06.000
Cut it off, Robin.

01:06:06.000 --> 01:06:08.000
I'm coming with you, Josie.

01:06:09.000 --> 01:06:12.000
What are you all doing on your own mat?

01:06:12.000 --> 01:06:14.000
Come back here.

01:06:14.000 --> 01:06:16.000
What a day.

01:06:16.000 --> 01:06:18.000
What a holiday.

01:06:18.000 --> 01:06:21.000
I don't understand the English.

01:06:21.000 --> 01:06:25.000
They are very, very strange people.

01:06:25.000 --> 01:06:27.000
Look.

01:06:27.000 --> 01:06:29.000
Oh, my God.

01:06:38.000 --> 01:06:40.000
Thank you.

